text:
after you have identified those who have wounded you, the next step to your healing is forgiving them. this is not because they aren't wrong for wounding you, it's simply releasing them from your heart. when genuinely done, this act removes resentment, bitterness and anger and invites god's healing virtues to occupy your wounded soul.

text:
📝herstory📝: .
.
“a family moved next door to me. they seemed really nice until i realized the husband was beating the wife and 2 little kids regularly. i called the cops every single time i heard him. i’ll never forget the sound of it. they moved exactly 1 year later.”
.
.
i’m a mandated reporter myself. i take that responsibility seriously. i remember when i myself was approached as an adult by a family friend, asking if i was okay and if i needed help getting out of a violent relationship myself. i was so offended at the time, soooooo offended. i knew deep down she was right and my life didn’t make sense. i sent her thanks years later for tipping me off that i needed to change and she could tell. i’ll always be thankful for that one moment i realized she was right and to her for having the guts to give it to me straight. -💜❤️vu
.
.
thank you for sending in ‘yourstories’ to @vaginasunitedvu . it means so much to us and to the women you are sharing ‘yourstory’ with. 💕
.
.

text:
from one mom to all of you mamas out there: 
after my babies were born, there were appointments.

to check their latch.

to check their weight.

to check their hearing. 
to check the colour of their skin for signs of jaundice.

there were appointments.

there were regular pokes and prods.

their well-being was front and centre. 
i'd say, when it comes to our health-care system, they were well taken care of.

then there was me.

a first-time mom without a clue. 
engorged, bleeding, and stitched up.

sent home with some painkillers and stool softeners.

thrown into motherhood with the expectation my instincts would kick in.

that i would know how to handle colic and late night feedings.

that breastfeeding would come as nature intended. 
that my husband would sense my spiral into depression.

that i would know how to live in my new and very foreign body. 
that this stomach wouldn't make me feel hideous.

and my mind wouldn't make me feel less than they deserved.

no one poked me.

no one prodded.

no one checked my stitches, my healing, or my sanity until eight weeks postpartum.

and even then, it was a pat on the back and i was sent on my way.

our world forgets about mothers.

we slip through the cracks.

we become background noise.

and in that, we learn our role... our place in our family unit... to always come last.

folks, we can't put mothers last.

our babies need us. 
to be healthy.

to know that we are worthy.

to know that motherhood, while natural, can sometimes feel like the least natural role in our life.

and that deserves attention. 
mothers deserve attention.

we need our world to fuss over us the way they fuss over ten fresh fingers and ten fresh toes.

we need to be seen.

we need to be heard.

we need someone to not only ask if we're okay but to check time and time again, just to be sure. 
we're not just a uterus.

we're not just a lifeline to a new and precious soul. 
we're mothers.

and we need someone to make sure we're ok, too. (anonymous)

text:
*review*
.
yes! yes! yes! this was the kind of book about hades and persephone that i really wanted to read! this was everything i desperately craved for and even more. but most of all: this were hades and persephone as i really imagined them, based on the original greek myths. the personalities of all the gods were spot on and very well done. and i might have enjoyed zeus being called out quite a bit too much.

let me start with writing down that this is not really a retelling. as in, this is not a modern au or some other twist on the myths that have been passed down for generations. this is actually for the most part the myth as we know, but with some slight touches that fit the modern need of women like me, and with some other mythologies, especially troy, tied into it. but, the language of the book feels a little old fashioned at times, a little much tell and not always show and very flowery. after a while i got used to it and i find it very fitting, but it's not the easy to read ya you might expect.

i however really enjoyed reading this book so much. this is partly because the two perspectives, hades and persephone, are both very insightful. we really get to know them both, in all their glory and with all their flaws and strengths. and we get to witness them falling for each other and them making each others lives and worlds better.

but, we most of all experience how persephone blossoms into an independent woman, taking charge and learning that her suggestions are important, that she can make a difference and that she can really help those who need her most.

at the end of the book i realised that i've been reading a story about female empowerment and calling out the male pigs that prevented us from pursuing it.
.
.
#hadesandpersephone #erinkinsella #hades #persephone #greekmythology #feminism #metoo #femaleempowerment #bookish #bookworm #bookstagram #booklovers #reading #reader #bookdragon

text:
i spent the weekend processing some rage. because the parallels are hitting that tipping point again. the parallels between the “leadership” in our country and an abusive relationship.
•
dangling a segment of our working population over the edge of a cliff and then jerking them back to solid ground after f*cking with them mercilessly for over a month does not deserve a round of applause. the changing whims of the perpetrator does not make him a hero! it makes him demonstrably sick.
•

text:
hoy en #mujeres recordamos a virginia woolf.
1882-1941.
escritora y feminista.
.
reconocida por su ensayo "una habitación propia". un texto feminista.
.
donde examina la situación de las mujeres escritoras y dice que "una mujer debe tener dinero y una habitación propia para escribir novelas".
.
inventa un personaje, judith shakespeare", donde manifiesta como una mujer, con iguales habilidades a william shakespeare, se debía quedar en casa mientras su hermano sí podía ir a la escuela. mostrando la situación de muchas mujeres en su época, "limitadas por las expectativas sociales de ser mujer".
.
¿hemos avanzado?¿las limitaciones de las mujeres son menos ahora? ¿o todo sigue siendo muy similar?🤔 ¿las mujeres tenemos ya las mismas oportunidades? .
.
.
.
.
.
#virginiawoolf #feminismo #feministas #feminist #equidaddegenero #genderequality

text:
we're going to need more wine by gabrielle union is not your typical celebrity memoir. she begins the book by sharing that's she going to tell the stories she's only ever shared with her closest girlfriends. i rolled my eyes at this, thinking that's what everyone says.  i was very wrong. •

union, who is called nicki by friends and family, shares it all in this book.  she writes candidly about her failed marriage,  being famous, being raped at gunpoint,  colorism, her prenup with her current husband basketball superstar dwyane wade, their struggle with infertility and what it's like raising black teenagers.  i'm not even sure i share this much personal stuff with my closest girlfriends. •

i watched the oprah interview, after i finished the book.  it's really good too, have you watched it? •

text:
heartfelt congrats to #bgbactor, @mandolinkelly, for running to be a democratic delegate in assembly district 51!! this is what using your voice looks like‼️ and while everyone might fight for their mission in different ways, choosing to fight is what is important. congratulations madeline on making the bold decision to stand in your power and fight for something you believe in.
____
madeline's statement: "i believe that we can create a regenerative economy in california, and forge a green new deal that improves our community and elevates our state. i stand for healthcare for all, affordable housing, debt free college, and living wages. i want to listen to your ideas and spread them. we have untapped strength in our diversity and more voices need to be listened to and upheld. together, we can create real opportunities that cross barriers of identity and economic status.
____ 
after two years of organizing in the community, i have been on the front lines of social advocacy in los angeles. as an organizer for public banking (measure b) the sunrise movement, divest la, and #metoo, i am deeply connected to the grassroots call for change from our representatives and party leadership. i have marched alongside you, and gone to our representatives to change policy on behalf of the people. i will bring a progressive, solution-focused conversation to our california democratic party. it is not enough to have good ideas, but we need leadership that fosters bravery in these times, and we must put forward solutions to create a better tomorrow, for our people and our planet. i will listen to you, and fight for what matters to you, so that our party will better represent the long term interests of the people over the short term interests of the few. i am proud to be a part of the working progressives for ad 51 slate, alongside many other long term community members and advocates."
💪🏻💪🏻💪🏻💪🏻
what's something you fight for? let us know below 👇🏻

text:
come audition for gift horse’s debut production of tess of the d’urbervilles, supported by the trinity visual and performing arts fund. 
a lively, daring adaptation of thomas hardy’s controversial novel, this production will take place outside in trinity’s rose garden. a  spirited ensemble will tell tess’ story, supported by a live band and a cast of colourful characters. considered in the light of the #metoo movement, how do we reevaluate tess and her story? 
this production is part of gift horse’s aim to move towards an environmentally conscious theatre - all costumes will be ethically sourced, for example.

text:
@beyondbeautifulint - a catwalk event management & productions event focused on women, make up, skincare, hair care and also, women empowerment. 
it was a well planned event in terms of the fact that all the important aspects of #grooming were taken into consideration. various men and women from different walks of life were called in and discussions were held on topics from health to the #metoo movement. there were lots of sponsors which had put up stalls with free #consultation and some stalls offered free goodies too including @physiogelpakistan , @pondspk , @conatural, @lorealmakeup etc. 👍

the highlight of the event for me was the “master class by @nabila_salon ”. although, it started a little late but was totally worth it! nabila is a wonderful woman who explained how to #prepare for and carry out make up for a #covershoot. it was unusual as such topics aren’t covered in a typical masterclass and she’s the queen of make up anyway. what i learnt was that there are really no rules to be followed when it comes to make up, go with what looks beautiful and appealing! i will put up a video soon of the unwrapping of the #zeroblendingbrush they gave in the goodies, super excited to use it in my upcoming tutorial. 
i strongly believe, such events should be organised on a regular bases, as it gives women from all classes to come on the same platform and learn how to be what they #deserve to be - #gorgeous inside out!

#catwalk #beyondbeautifulpakistan #makeup #nabilas #panel #beauty #style #ponds 
#physiogel #conatural #loreal #masterclass #queenofmakeup #review #experience

text: ⚫️: terry crews, celui à gauche sur la vidéo au-dessus, a récemment admit avoir été agressé sexuellement par son agent. depuis, plusieurs célébrités (hommes) se sont carrément moqués de lui ne comprenant pas comment un homme "de sa taille" peut se faire agresser sexuellement. le comédien dl hughley a dit dans cette itw ci-dessus: " a penser qu'un mec avec tous ses muscles ne peut même pas dire à son agent de ne pas toucher son cul... je comprends pas. je crois que tout le monde est dans cette phase de "me too (balance ton porc)", et "ça met arrivé aussi", .. mec dieu t'a donné des muscles pour que tu puisses dire non." suite à ça, terry crews à tweeté à dl hughley (traduction des tweets au dessus) : "toi, 50 cent, unclerush et tariqnasheed avaient tous décidés que mon agression sexuelle était une blague marrante alors qu'il y a  toute une génération de femmes et hommes noirs qui ne trouvent pas sa drôle du tout. les abuseurs protègent les abuseurs mais ce moquent aussi des survivants. quand tu me vois, trace ta route." autre tweet: "tu es maintenant un exemple de quand la comédie devient satirique et cynique. et tu trouves ça très facile de faire des blagues au détriment d'autrui. tu te moques de mon succès alors que je t'ai toujours supporté.”

text:
well, here goes an adventure... i’m continually prompted to write and share my writing, so i’m finally taking the plunge. 
if you or someone you know has experienced abuse - if someone you love is surviving it, i encourage you to join and share my new blog. it’s raw. it’s real. it’s for healing and company on the road. 
i’m going through the workbook, shelter from the storm, hope for survivors if sexual abuse, 
by cynthia kubetin. i’ll reference this book so if you want to pick one up, we’ll be able to chat about it and reflect together. or you can just read my own reflections. www.teresabruce.blog #timesup

text:
“nothing in life so isolates us from healthy human relationships and from a relationship with god as does sexual abuse. any experience of sexual abuse - but especially child sexual abuse - violates our boundaries and our trust.”
-shelter from the storm

it was a very rough week following my first blog post. i wrote through tears and all week the tears just kept coming. not in a hopeless way, more of a thawing and releasing. the experience of my adopted father, don, choking me unconscious was frozen in time, locked deep-freeze within me.

you can retell and think about all the stories with no problem. it’s feeling about them - the lack of feeling about them that gets you stopped up. i was happy to not feel about them. i believed, “frozen is good”, but how many of us know what frostbite looks like? what does it feel like? how does it taste? 
i’m unpacking the frozen parts, to thaw and slack off their ice so they can heal. you can join me www.teresabruce.blog this week’s blog title is, the big thaw. #metoo #timesup #sexualabusesurvivorsstories #assaultsurvivor #childabuse #abuse #inspirational #christianblogger #hope

text:
my sweet loves getting much needed rest by the fire. there’s nothing better than seeing them safe, cozy and content in my home. for many years that was not the case. we walked on eggshells, didn’t feel safe, and never truly felt at ease. so this picture holds so much more meaning than what meets the eye. that i made it out. that i created a life for the 3 of us that is based on love, trust and unconditional love. no more fear. no more walking on eggshells. no more enduring rages that took their innocence and my self esteem. no more put downs. no more waiting for the other shoe to drop. no more hiding who we are and what we think to appease someone who just wanted control. no more fear of losing my children to made up accusations. no more court that caused so much anxiety, i couldn’t sleep, eat or breathe. in 2014 my babies were stolen from me with a slew of lies and fabrications. it almost killed me. that kind of fear, loss and having no control changes a person. though justice prevailed the fear didn’t end. it’s taken years of hard work, grueling work to get here. and i’m not the same person in so many good ways but also ways that have left me having a hard time trusting life; trusting people; trusting the process; trusting the universe to right the wrongs. i’m still working on that. 
it’s solely on me now physically, financially, and emotionally to protect them, nurture them, provide for them. it shouldn’t be that a parent can decide that to continue to punish me, by bowing out of responsibilities that hurt the children. but that’s our reality. because of this i’ve struggled, hard. i’ve struggled to see through the anger. i’ve struggled to understand. i’ve struggled trying to let go of so much anger, too much anger that it was detrimental to my health, my heart and my belief in humanity. anger ruled my head and my heart for too long. creating questions i couldn’t find answers to. why? what kind of parent does this? why do they get away with it? why does our system have really no way to right this wrong? how can someone be this angry and cruel? how do they live with themselves? 
i still don’t have answers to the millions of questions (cont in comments)

my sweet loves getting much needed rest by the fire. there’s nothing better than seeing them safe, cozy and content in my home. for many years that was not the case. we walked on eggshells, didn’t feel safe, and never truly felt at ease. so this picture holds so much more meaning than what meets the eye. that i made it out. that i created a life for the 3 of us that is based on love, trust and unconditional love. no more fear. no more walking on eggshells. no more enduring rages that took their innocence and my self esteem. no more put downs. no more waiting for the other shoe to drop. no more hiding who we are and what we think to appease someone who just wanted control. no more fear of losing my children to made up accusations. no more cou that caused so much anxiety, i couldn’t sleep, eat or breathe. in 2014 my babies were stolen from me with a slew of lies and fabrications. it almost killed me. that kind of fear, loss and having no control changes a person. though justice prevailed the fear didn’t end. it’s taken years of hard work, grueling work to get here. and i’m not the same person in so many good ways but also ways that have left me having a hard time trusting life; trusting people; trusting the process; trusting the universe to right the wrongs. i’m still working on that. 
it’s solely on me now physically, ficially, and emotionally to protect them, nuure them, provide for them. it shouldn’t be that a parent can decide that to continue to punish me, by bowing out of responsibilities that hu the children. but that’s our reality. because of this i’ve struggled, hard. i’ve struggled to see through the anger. i’ve struggled to understand. i’ve struggled trying to let go of so much anger, too much anger that it was detrimental to my health, my hea and my belief in humanity. anger ruled my head and my hea for too long. creating questions i couldn’t find answers to. why? what kind of parent does this? why do they get away with it? why does our system have really no way to right this wrong? how can someone be this angry and cruel? how do they live with themselves? 
i still don’t have answers to the millions of questions (cont in comments)

text:
hur vet man vem man är och vad man vill? hur känns puberteten? vad menas med bra sex? vad menas med jämställdhet?
.
dessa frågor och många fler får svar i ”viktigast av allt -om kroppen, känslor och sex”. nathalie simonsson har i många år jobbat med ungdomar på rfsu och tröttnade på att den sexualundervisning som ges i skolan fortfarande är lika mossig som när hon själv gick i skolan. hon tog tag i saken och skrev först ”världens viktigaste bok -om kroppen, känslor och sex” för mellanstadiet. med uppföljaren, ”viktigast av allt”, vänder hon sig till högstadieåldern och fokuserar på de frågor och funderingar som uppstår då. böckerna är illustrerade i mangastil av yosh tam.
.
”viktigast av allt” bygger på åtskilliga samtal som nathalie haft med barn och ungdomar och frågor som de ställt. i sviterna av #metoo har det blivit ännu tydligare hur mycket denna typ av böcker behövs. som belyser känslor, jämställdhet, kroppens förändringar i puberteten, familjerelationer, psykisk ohälsa och mens m.m.
.
se boken som ett storasyskon eller en vän och sätt den i handen på närmsta 12-15-åring i din närhet. för barn i 9-12-årsåldern rekommenderas istället ”världens viktigaste bok” som recenserats och tipsats om flera ggr tidigare. bägge böckerna är ett måste i skolbiblioteken och rekommenderas varmt att även använda i undervisningen, till den för mellanstadiet finns även lärarhandledning.
.
för dig som vill köpa någon av böckerna finns länkar i stories och på bloggen.
.

text: here is an example of a strong “asian” woman my mother in 1978 purchased a 1972 corvette after working two jobs: bullocks makeup department and moonlighting to cbs networks. she never complained like todays feminist movement #feminist #metoo and she was hit on by males at cbs but all she had to do was say “no” my dad showed up to cbs with a baseball bat in 1984 lol regardless she did what she needed to do that was right and not complain. keep in mind that this was the 70s and women’s suffrage was only settled alongside the civil rights movement in the 1960s. this is why i do not agree or support movies like “crazy rich asians” because it does not depict the asian community and its entirety . #women #1972 #corvette #civilrights #gm #chevrolet #asians

text:
بالتأكيد ، شرينو باريخ لا يمكن أن تطلب بداية أفضل من هذه  لعام 2019 . الممثلة الجميلة من فادودارا ، التي تصدرت عناوين الصحف لجميع الأسباب الصحيحة في الأشهر القليلة الماضية ( فازت بقلوب بعجبيها ب غوري في ishqbaaaz ، قدمت اول  عمل لها  في أفلام الغوجاراتية مع خيزران راستو ........
وحازت الآن على الدور الرائد في  برنامج تلفزيوني قادم مثير ، وقد تم التصويت عليها من قبل المعجبين باسم أحمد آباد لأكثر امرأة  مرغوب فيها  للعام الثاني على التوالي . و هذا لا تُعد مفاجأة ، مع الأخذ بعين الاعتبار  تواصل شرينو  تحسينها  نفسها  مع كل مشروع جديد وتديره لزيادة قاعدة المعجبين بها بشكل منتظم ، وذلك بفضل شخصيتها المحببة والطبيعة السهلة .لا ننسى صوتها الرخيم وابتسامتها الساحرة ، وشعبيتها المتزايدة على منصات التواصل الاجتماعي .عندما علمت بفوزها كانت شرينو بفادودرا ، وقالت مازحة😊 : " أنا فقط عاجزة عن الكلام ! أنا ممتنة حقاً لأحمد آباد تايمز وكل المشجعين الذين جعلوا هذا ممكناً مرة : أخرى . "😍😍 ما هي أفكارك حول اختيارك  كأكثر امرأة مرغوبة عام 2018 ؟: هذا الحب الذي لا ينتهي من معجبي ساحق . بصراحة ، كانت النتائج مفاجأة سارة . تماما مثل العام الماضي ، كنت أنتظر بفارغ الصبر نتائج الاستطلاع ، لكنني لم أكن أتوقع حقا الفوز للسنة الثانية على التوالي . إنه شعور هائل للحصول على أكبر عدد من الأصوات بين بعض النساء الرائعات من مختلف المجالات ، اللواتي يستحقن نفس القدر . أود فقط أن أعرب عن امتناني  لكل من أيدني . هذه هي أفضل ! هدية العام الجديد بالنسبة لي .....
** وفقا لك ، ما هي الصفات التي تجعلك مرغوبا فيها ؟ :
مثلما قلت العام الماضي ، هناك الكثير منها . أنا شخص لا يفرط في الأشياء ، وأنا أحاول دائما أن أكون نفسي . معجبيني  يعرفونني على حقيقتي ، يعرفون كيف أبدو
 بدون مكياج ، أنهم يحبونني .هم ينتقدونني أيضا .أعتقد أنني كنت دائماً ألتقي بتوقعاتهم ولقد عملت بجد من أجل ذلك .معجباتي يحبون نوع الشخص الذي أنا عليه  وأحب التفاعل معهم .
**من هو ، حسب رأيكم ، أكثر الرجال والنساء المرغوبين في الهند ؟

رانبير كابور هو الرجل الأكثر جاذبية في الهند ، ولقد كان دائما سحق عليه . بين النساء ، تستحق . علياء بهات وديبيكا بادوكوني ذلك اللقب
👇👇👇👇

وحازت الآن على الدور الرائد في  برنامج تلفزيوني قادم مثير ، وقد تم التصويت عليها من قبل المعجبين باسم أحمد آباد لأكثر امرأة  مرغوب فيها  للعام الثاني على التوالي . و هذا لا تُعد مفاجأة ، مع الأخذ بعين الاعتبار  تواصل شرينو  تحسينها  نفسها  مع كل مشروع جديد وتديره لزيادة قاعدة المعجبين بها بشكل منتظم ، وذلك بفضل شخصيتها المحببة والطبيعة السهلة .لا ننسى صوتها الرخيم وابتسامتها الساحرة ، وشعبيتها المتزايدة على منصات التواصل الاجتماعي .عندما علمت بفوزها كانت شرينو بفادودرا ، وقالت مازحة😊 : " أنا فقط عاجزة عن الكلام ! أنا ممتنة حقاً لأحمد آباد تايمز وكل المشجعين الذين جعلوا هذا ممكناً مرة : أخرى . "😍😍 ما هي أفكارك حول اختيارك  كأكثر امرأة مرغوبة عام 2018 ؟: هذا الحب الذي لا ينتهي من معجبي ساحق . بصراحة ، كانت النتائج مفاجأة سارة . تماما مثل العام الماضي ، كنت أنتظر بفارغ الصبر نتائج الاستطلاع ، لكنني لم أكن أتوقع حقا الفوز للسنة الثانية على التوالي . إنه شعور هائل للحصول على أكبر عدد من الأصوات بين بعض النساء الرائعات من مختلف المجالات ، اللواتي يستحقن نفس القدر . أود فقط أن أعرب عن امتناني  لكل من أيدني . هذه هي أفضل ! هدية العام الجديد بالنسبة لي .....
** وفقا لك ، ما هي الصفات التي تجعلك مرغوبا فيها ؟ :
مثلما قلت العام الماضي ، هناك الكثير منها . أنا شخص لا يفرط في الأشياء ، وأنا أحاول دائما أن أكون نفسي . معجبيني  يعرفونني على حقيقتي ، يعرفون كيف أبدو
 بدون مكياج ، أنهم يحبونني .هم ينتقدونني أيضا .أعتقد أنني كنت دائماً ألتقي بتوقعاتهم ولقد عملت بجد من أجل ذلك .معجباتي يحبون نوع الشخص الذي أنا عليه  وأحب التفاعل معهم .
**من هو ، حسب رأيكم ، أكثر الرجال والنساء المرغوبين في الهند ؟

رانبير كابور هو الرجل الأكثر جاذبية في الهند ، ولقد كان دائما سحق عليه . بين النساء ، تستحق . علياء بهات وديبيكا بادوكوني ذلك اللقب

text:
at 15, i attended a gems outreach group, while in a secure detention facility. i disclosed to the gems outreach coordinator and family court advocacy coordinator (fcac) a history of commercial sexual exploitation and pimp control, dating back to 12. i worked with the fcac individually, and after engaging in services for a year, i gave a presentation to my fellow residents. i was the only resident in the history of my detention facility to reach the highest level of behavior. i mentored my fellow residents, explaining that innovation was rooted in believing in my own potential.

text:
hvor ble det av januar? for første gang på mange, mange år har jeg hatt en januar uten mørke skyer. en januar uten smerter, og uten tunge dager. jeg har en tilstand som heter fibromyalgi, og håper og tror jeg nå har funnet den riktige balansen mellom trening, næring og aktivitetsnivå. fibromyalgi er en kronisk sykdom som beskrives som en forstyrrelse i sentralnervesystemets følsomhet. jeg er en ganske sammensatt person, som de siste årene har skjønt at helsa er det viktigste jeg har. jeg er en person som har tatt mine valg på grunnlag av akkurat den erkjennelsen. kroppen min tålte ikke 7 år med daglig sexuell trakassering på jobb. kroppen min tåler ikke negativt stress og støy, nettopp fordi min barndom besto av akkurat den kombinasjonen. i dag skulle jeg ønske at #metoo hadde kommet litt tidlige. kanskje jeg da hadde blitt tatt hensyn til hos min tidligere arbeidsgiver, adresseavisen, «midt-norges frie stemme»? fibromyalgi, byr på mye smerter i kroppen vinterstid, likevel er trening min medisin, og jeg elsker alt treningen gir meg: opplevelser, mestringsfølelse, smertelindring, nye venner, og en sprekere og mer fleksibel kropp. du som følger meg, vet at jeg har overlevd sexuelle overgrep som barn. du vet at jeg har overlevd årevis med vold og seksuell trakassering som barn. du vet at jeg har perioder med depresjoner, og i gitte situasjoner blir jeg også retraumatisert. likevel er jeg så mye mer enn alt dette. på innsiden er jeg et ungt menneske. jeg er kreativ og flink til veldig mye. tegne, designe, kommunisere, og skape gode øyeblikk for andre. ordene kommer lett i de sene nattetimer — eller som nå, med emilie nicolas på øret. jeg er glad for alle de historiene mennesker forteller meg i fortrolighet. akkurat det er en gave, og en tillitserklæring. jeg har mye å være glad for. livet er en reise, og på mandag starter et nytt kapittel... hvordan har januar vært for deg?
.

text:
let’s get intimate! guys like i mentioned in my first post, after being assaulted i struggled a lot with intimacy, i honestly would almost done out during sex. why? because of the negatives that accompanied it. the faster he is done the faster sex can be over. that’s what would go through my head, and honest it made my life miserable and was straining my relationship. my partner wanted to feel connected with me and i just wasn’t present. this year i have been focusing on me, i want to enjoy sex, i want to get intimate with my partner. so now i focus on being present. i focus on what is happening in that exact moment and i just try to be present. i have felt a deeper connection in this. we should not let our assault ruin our lives because it wasn’t our fault and we deserve that happiness. it took me so long to realize that sex doesn’t have to be negative!
.
.
.
.
.
#timesup #metoo #selfcare #selflove #movingforward #learningtolovemyself #survivor #endstigma #lovingmyself #thisisme

text:
not far from the #nanterre #faculty @uparisnanterre and beyond a #circus. after the large wooden door surmounted by a bronze bell, la @la_ferme_du_bonheur welcomes you across ornamental gardens, an #orchard, a vegetable garden of aromatic and medicinal, a horticultural #greenhouse, the whole in the center of @diocesenanterre.
before it was a raw yard, of 2500sqm, vestige of an old school from 1904, demolished in 1992, where stands now the "#favelatheater," a  self-built structure, very rustic, with second hand materials, completely transparent; hosting a convertible theater, dining room, dancefloor, steam room... where the family "is the pig" in winter. 
near to the ballroom, including the restaurant, with vintage furniture; completed by workshops construction costumes and scenery... all between the pigeon, the barn, the piggery, the backyard, the aviary, the career of horses... because before turning to a cultural project, la #fermedubonheur is a #farm, within at the origin, roger des prés, a former actor of the so-called "alternative rock" #1980s scene, staged shows that agrees to say "#theater", even if materials are not always texts, still today like: #dostoyevsky, outdoor #jeangiono stories with a herd of #sheeps in #transhumance, written policies or test radio of #jeangenet, #waltwhitman poetry...
in 1999, the @ministerecc has established a agreement with the ferme du bonheur, still in progress today... people celebrate their wedding in an amazing, political and poetic ritual. concretely, from the early hours of the creation of the farm, roger chose not to be the only one to create; thus, proposing to other artists, companies to distribute their works: theater, dance, scholarly and popular music, also film, visual arts... to mention a few: sophie lecarpentier, #jeannebalibar, alexis forest, jacques rebotier...
music: @abcmartinfry / the look of love (#remix)

text:
.
.
elections have consequences, part 296,375
🙃🙃🙃🙃🙃
.
.
.
.
.
“without fanfare or even notice, the department of justice’s office on violence against women made significant changes to its definition of domestic violence in april. the obama-era definition was expansive, vetted by experts including the national center for victims of crime and the national domestic violence hotline. the trump administration’s definition is substantially more limited and less informed, effectively denying the experiences of victims of abuse by attempting to cast domestic violence as an exclusively criminal concern.
.
.
.
the previous definition included critical components of the phenomenon that experts recognize as domestic abuse—a pattern of deliberate behavior, the dynamics of power and control, and behaviors that encompass physical or sexual violence as well as forms of emotional, economic, or psychological abuse. but in the trump justice department, only harms that constitute a felony or misdemeanor crime may be called domestic violence. so, for example, a woman whose partner isolates her from her family and friends, monitors her every move, belittles and berates her, or denies her access to money to support herself and her children is not a victim of domestic violence in the eyes of trump’s department of justice. this makes no sense for an office charged with funding and implementing solutions to the problem of domestic violence rather than merely prosecuting individual abusers.
.
.
.
for varied reasons, many survivors make an informed choice to not initiate a criminal case.
.
.
.
restoring nonphysical violence to the definition of domestic violence is critical. as the centers for disease control and prevention reports, over one-third of u.s. women (43.5 million) have experienced “psychological aggression” at the hands of an intimate partner. experts have long recognized that the manipulative behaviors identified in the obama-era definition as restricting a victim’s liberty or freedom can cause greater and more lasting damage than physical harm.”
.
.
.
more in the comments

we get these terms thrown at us for standing up for ourselves, and for what we believe in. it's important that we do, cos the message still hasn't got through to people. a man exposed himself to me today as i walked alone through an underpass. i told him where to fucking go, i can handle myself. but if i wasn't strong it could have been a different story. it's not the first time and probably won't be the last. .
.
.

.

text:
жизнь — болезнь материи, мышление — болезнь жизни. цитата из «гадких лебедей» стругацких. это слова о том, что живые организмы и мыслительный процесс объективно являются не высшим вселенским благом, а лишь случайностью, мутацией, одним из вариантов развития событий в огромном мире. жуком быть не лучше чем лавой или гравитацией, человеком быть не лучше, чем жуком или лианой. это просто по-другому. и то, и то неплохо.
.
плохо, когда понимаешь, что твоё мышление это в прямом смысле твоя болезнь. когда твои мысли, твои сны тебе не союзники. болезнь называется очень просто - негативное мышление. если вы выросли в россии, вам это хоть немного да будет знакомо. наш национальный спорт - перетаскивать тяжёлые мысли. из головы бабушки в голову мамы, из мамы в дочку, из учителя в ученика, из соседа в соседку, из кондуктора в пассажира, из врача в пациента.
.
сейчас я учусь мне-важно-мышлению. это когда ты говоришь себе «у меня никогда не будет читателей», и тут же себя поправляешь - мне важно иметь читателей. говоришь «я всегда буду так быстро уставать» и меняешь на - мне важно иметь много энергии. это может показаться очевидным и простым занятием, для кого-то вообще смешной мелочью. но я иду из тёмной пещеры маленькими шажками ✨
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

плохо, когда понимаешь, что твоё мышление это в прямом смысле твоя болезнь. когда твои мысли, твои сны тебе не союзники. болезнь называется очень просто - негативное мышление. если вы выросли в россии, вам это хоть немного да будет знакомо. наш национальный спорт - перетаскивать тяжёлые мысли. из головы бабушки в голову мамы, из мамы в дочку, из учителя в ученика, из соседа в соседку, из кондуктора в пассажира, из врача в пациента.
.
сейчас я учусь мне-важно-мышлению. это когда ты говоришь себе «у меня никогда не будет читателей», и тут же себя поправляешь - мне важно иметь читателей. говоришь «я всегда буду так быстро уставать» и меняешь на - мне важно иметь много энергии. это может показаться очевидным и простым занятием, для кого-то вообще смешной мелочью. но я иду из тёмной пещеры маленькими шажками ✨
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
несколько безрадостных дней я провела, изучая страшную тему педофилии. с понятным стремлением узнать, есть ли способы уберечь ребёнка от контакта с хищником, кроме как водить его всюду за руку (кратко: нет, особо нету).
⠀
выяснила следующее. педофилами называются люди, испытывающие половое влечение к детям допубертатного возраста (0-13 лет).
⠀
влечение к детям - тема глубоко табуированная, исследований по ней мало, но канадские психиатры cantor и malo считают, что 0,5-1% мужчин являются педофилами.
⠀
педофилы внутри группы длятся на pro-contact и non-contact: первая группа с живыми детьми контактирует, вторая - нет.
⠀
понятно, что с родительской точки зрения опаснее группа pro-contact, поскольку у них есть целая богатая идеология, объясняющая, почему секс с детьми - это хорошо, полезно и правильно для всех участников. эта идеология прекрасно гуглится на обоих языках, но не советую.
⠀
таких людей в своём окружении вычислить практически невозможно - при том, что 3/4 случаев насилия над детьми совершают родственники и близкие к семье люди. в 90% случаев насильника знают и ребёнок, и родители. (под насилием я понимаю любой сексуальный контакт с ребёнком).
⠀
на этом моменте я сильно загрустила и провела пару дней в тщетных поисках психологического профиля pro-сontact педофила.
⠀
британские специалисты (ссылки будут в комментах) пишут, что стоит насторожиться, если взрослый или молодой человек: ⤵️

text:
his demeanor changed. once i heard his belt buckle hit the floor, he started to move with panic. i could feel him breathing really hard on my neck. and no matter how hard i fought and resisted, he got my pants down to my ankles. and before i could even take another breath, he was inside of me.

as i wrote that, my stomach turned. i love to write but there will never be a set of words that could ever describe what it's like to have something… someone inside of you… without your personal invitation.

i honestly don't remember how i got away. it was just 5… maybe 10 seconds of my body being invaded but 5-10 way too many.

but like i always do, i wiped my tears… fixed my clothes… and walked out like i was fine before asking my friend if we could leave.
and immediately i felt... guilty.
//
this is just a small snippet of my new blogpost the belt buckle. this is my #metoo story but by the grace of god i was also able to tell 66 other stories from so many beautiful women (and a few brave men). follow the link in my bio for the full story! i hope whoever needs healing receives this. i hope the misguided receive this. i hope you receive it. ❤️

text: blast from the past - band was called filthy dukes and the song is this rhythm. this must be at least 12 years ago by now, maybe even longer, and the band was at the time very underground cool. my longest working collab director, the great @sarahjchatfield directed this (when there weren’t that many female directors around). if i’m not mistaken, this was shot on 35mm and with old lomo anamorphic lenses. might have been my own set that i had purchased (but sadly no longer own). not sure. in any case, the clip is rather grainy and i remember we pushed the exposures pretty daringly. it’s a dark piece, both literally and conceptually. i used to favor fuji stock at the time (it was more budget friendly than kodak), so there’s a high risk this was shot on that. if i were to guess, i’d say their low contrast 400t stock, most likely. it was a favorite at the time. sadly, which i regret a lot, is i have no notes on equipment or stocks for my earlier work, so it’s all guesswork. even more sad is that all videos then were telecined and colored in sd, so there will never be hd version of these older videos. too costly (and sometimes even impossible) to go back to locate the negatives and do a hd transfer and conform again. it’s extra sad, because at the time hd was already a thing, but the record companies had no foresight and no desire to pay for the slightly more expensive hd transfers. i bet they regret that today with youtube and all the social media.... anyway, back to video - it was shot in some old school outside of london, all in a day. the actress, gia, had a great face that photographed well. i remember we ran out of time on last set, which was elaborate in sarah’s mind, so had to rush through it in both the build and shooting of it. good times. @gialazarova #filthydukes #fuji400t #lomo #lomoanamorphic #arri #arri435 #sd #musicvideo #metoo #femaledirector #telecine

text:
i told him everything about me. he didn't run. i told him about my deepest darkest secrets. he wasn't frightened. i told him that i didn't need someone to save me. he stood by my side. 
there was a part of me that was scared as hell and the other that said it's time. i shared my story knowing that for some it may be too much and for others it was exactly what they needed to know that they are not alone. 
and as i cried he held me tightly. he's my silent samurai.

text:
in exactly 2 months from today we’ll be embarking on an incredible journey alongside 9 brave women. this is where acceptance, self-love, reconciliation and redemption will be born. this is where women will take back the power that their trauma and pain have held over their lives for too long. women will be set free, filled with hope and peace, and find a community of women that will undoubtedly become family.
.
for those who have decided to take this brave step...we commend you, we’re in awe of you, we support you, and we thank you for trusting us to help you carry and release the weight of your pain. it all starts here...two months from now.
.
for those of you who are still considering joining us on this transformational journey, those of you still on the ledge....we urge you take the plunge. we can’t promise you it won’t be hard, but we can promise you you’ll leave changed, empowered, and better than you were before.
.
we are officially sold out of single rooms but still have a few double and bunk bed accommodations available. we’d recommend signing up asap, as we can’t guarantee spots will stay open. see you in the mountains ladies!

text:
i am so fucking glad i had kids when social media wasn’t around. 
all the little social media demons making moms feel bad about the decisions she makes for her kids. 🤦🏻‍♀️
midwife or dr
hospital or birthing center
pushing baby out of vag or a horrible lower abdomen cut
breastfeeding or bottle 
formula or breast milk 
cloth diapers or disposable 
co-sleep or baby in crib
stay at home or work
dress up everyday or wear sweats
workout or just get out of bed
⬆️ is a lot of shit to be judged on ⬇️
you do you boo & what is best for your kid & yourself 
remember you were you before you were a mom
👊🏼💪🏻💋
.
.
.
.

text:
❄️💙☀️
i remember a nice winter
all there was was snow
i sled around the neighborhood 
knowing exactly where to go..
i know what i was feeling
the thrill of letting go
my vision clearly 
on the road..
i was drawn like a magnet 
to the universal flow
the rhythm of surrender grabbed my attention 
it carried me on..
i felt like i was on a journey 
specially designed for me
knowing no one would ever live
exactly like me..
i gave myself over 
all there was was snow
it turned out to be an adventurous ride
leading me home..
i know what i was feeling 
the experience alone
held all sorts of meaning 
waiting to be explored..
i remember a nice winter
all there was was snow
since then everything changed..
..not so much
still sledding around the neighborhood 
with soul
🙏

text:
le livre féministe à lire! #metoo #noshamefist #timesup 
à l’inverse des prises de position rétrogrades et culpabilisantes qui visent à inhiber ou à opposer, ce livre réunit les « prises de parole » et les « prises d’écriture » d’autrices et d’auteurs – militantes et militants, chercheuses et chercheurs, créatrices et créateurs, victimes ou non… -, qui, sans nier leurs divergences, s’accordent pour dénoncer les injustices et les violences réelles (professionnelles, économiques, sexuelles…) subies par les femmes aujourd’hui et réaffirment la nécessité de les penser et de les combattre. « cours petite fille », un livre collectif sous la direction de samuel lequette et delphine le vergos publié par éditions des femmes-antoinette fouque. en librairie le 31 janvier ! 
je suis fière de participer avec mon texte aux côté entre autres de asia argento, catharine mackinnon, michelle perrot, wendy delorme, fatima benomar, maïa mazaurette... #femen #feminist #feminism #womensmarch #womenempowerment #innashevchenko

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
but every writer, renowned or self-proclaimed, stops to think whether this silsila (chain) of endless pain would end if they stopped writing. it doesn't. it won't.
those people then spit venom through their spoken words.
i know because i am that person
___________

the roots of this poem is in the stories that unfolded during the #metoo movement. i didn't speak much then because i was just dumbfounded, at a loss of words because many of the predators were men i held in high regard. i did not doubt the stories of those women but i could not believe these men could have done such a horrible thing, including men who called themselves feminists. slowly as i read people and their views i could finally believe that yes! writers could be very wrong in reality and farrr from whom we think them to be! just because they've a gift of weaving words beautifully does not make them a righteous person. they could be anything and we won't know. this realisation also applies to me. many a times people take me to be a very good person though i'm like everyone - flawed.

text:
wo (against) men? 👩🏽⚔️🧔🏽
—
it’s been over one year since the #metoo - idea established in the context of the accusations against harvey weinstein in oktober 2017. 
us-american actress alyssa milano started the movement through asking #women to rise up and talk open about their experiences with sexual harassment, discrimination and abuse.
the hashtag developed in one year into a globally known movement that deals with #equality of man and women. 
as a result many victims finally talked openly about their experiences and especially cases of people of the public have been disclosed such as george w. bush or kevin spacey. both were accused of abusing their authority to harass several women.
—
even though the hashtag has triggered a huge sensation, on personal level and in developing countries where access to the internet is only limited and where the inequality of women and men is way more profound this movement couldn’t achieve anything.
—
it’s still a long way to go till change reaches a global level, but we won’t give up.
—
to what extend is it ok for men to approach women? what do you think? 
#women #girls #strongandproud #womensmovement #feminism #equality #foreveryone #oneworld #rights #freedom #happiness #children #makechange #wecandoit #lastwave #power #empowerment #noviolence 
#helpibri 
#behelpibri

crews is brave for speaking out; perpetuating the stigma is why so many violators continue to get away with it.

text:
so potty training update - yeah, well..it lasted two days and now we aren’t.
and you know what – it’s ok!
i pushed hard two of my other ones.
ive been relaxed with a few. 
and the easiest one to potty train (by far!) could not wake up dry until he was six or seven years old. nothing was wrong just a very deep sleeper.
i say all this to say, mama relax! it’s not a race! i repeat...not a race!
maybe it’s not potty training – maybe it’s reading, maybe it’s behavior, maybe it’s...anything. just take a breath!
i realize full well sometimes there are things for us to be genuinely concerned about (i have those too) but i dare say when you take a breath and you stop comparing your child to your other children or someone else’s children you might just see a little clearer, worry a little less, an be reminded they might be created with this struggle for a very specific purpose. (ask me how i know...)
you know, just for any of the other moms out there that can say - “me too!”
.
. .

text:
i only made it to episode 4 of #survivingrkelly before the panic attacks got to be too much. but the women and girls in the story, especially those who are still his prisoners, don’t have the option of chilling out and switching to bob’s burgers—they are in a nightmare every day. (incidentally, @bobsburgersfox included an “age ain’t nothing but a number” reference, from tina’s mouth no less, that made me sick to my stomach, that made me feel like women and girls have absolutely no one to trust in this world. ) 
girls are people. girls of color are people. how long until our society stops seeing them as fodder, as deserving of stupid, thoughtless jokes, as unworthy of justice? #muterkelly #sayhername #metoo #blacklivesmatter 
i don’t think a #watercolor has ever helped me feel so much anger.

text:
i’m a firm believer that your workspace should have 3 things: something that encourages you to learn, something that reminds you of where you’re going & something that brings you joy! .
.
when i worked in the food court at the mall these 3 things were present & now in my corporate job they are present. it’s only up until now that i could put words to why these 3 things are important to me. .
.
you see i recently did a study on how to control your environment after watching the movie ‘den of thieves’.. (although he controlled the environment to commit a crime )🙈 i wanted to control my environment to up my productivity & decrease the distractions! .
.
in all of the articles i read the common thing was to write out the places you spend the most time and then give that place a name + write down the things you will do in that place. .
.
however, i opted to give each place 2-3 bible verses; because ultimately i’m just a steward & everything i have belongs to god. .
.
so, here’s my challenge for you —if you feel like you’re just going through the motion, overly emotional, reacting and worried often, want to increase your productivity or just need some organization in your life. .
.
maybe giving your space a name or scripture is for you. we’re called to have self control & 2019 is your year to live out that truth!

#leavingneverland premieres at the #sundancefilm festival, has mixed reviews. the 4 hour docuseries chronicles the stories of two men who have claimed that the now deceased #michaeljackson, sexually abused them for years. neither was paid to appear in the film and say that they just wanted to bring awareness to the situation. when it was shown at the film festival, michael’s camp called it both outrageous and pathetic. #waderobinson and #jamessafechuck recount their experiences with the #kingofpop, saying that from ages 7 and 10 jackson reached out to them. wade claims that michael once told him that they were brought together by god, while wade recalls a mock wedding that he and jackson had to which he still has the rings and showed the camera. robson testified on behalf of jackson in the 2003 case against him, though both men later sued jackson’s estate. in the documentary, the men both say that they’ve spent years dealing with the psychological fallout from jackson’s abuse. fans around the world have responded to the film with some even protesting outside the theater where the movie premiered. the film is set to air later this year on hbo. what are your thoughts on this story? comment below.

text:
in april, changes were made to the definitions of domestic violence and sexual assault appearing on the website of the department of justice’s office of violence against women.

these changes represent a shift to a more narrow definition of domestic violence and sexual assault, defining them through the criminal justice lens. however, the overwhelming majority of sexual assault and majority of domestic violence cases are not reported. and those that are reported rarely move forward to an arrest.

we are here for support 24/7: (516)542-0404

text:
this week on insight, i interviewed an incredibly brave human being. daniel goldberg is a survivor of sexual assault- and he decided to go public with his story on social media so that other people would not fall victim to his attacker. 1 in 6 men have experienced sexual assault, but shockingly around 90% of the people that responded to his story on facebook were women. most men chose to send private messages of solidarity. it is a problem that this issue is so taboo. the #metoo movement applies to men and women alike, and advocates like daniel need to continue taking a stand. @capdain 
if you want to watch this episode, please go to my facebook page @natasharktv.

text:
in japan, broken objects are often repaired with gold. the process is called kintsugi. instead of throwing away a broken piece or trying to hide it, they highlight it. the flaw is seen as a unique piece of the object's history, which adds to its beauty. think about this when you feel broken.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
our wounds in life are part of us. when we try to ignore or hide them, we are left in pieces. let us take time to tend to our broken pieces.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
with broken pieces from things we did that we regret, may we make any amends we can, may we make peace with our self, and may we accept this piece of our story.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
with broken pieces from wounds caused by life or others, may we do healing things such as share with friends, journal, pray, talk with a counselor, and practice self-care. through processing what happened and experiencing some healing, we are able to continue in life with these broken pieces. they are no longer something we try to keep hidden. we no longer see them only as markers of pain, but we also them telling the story of what we did with that pain. reminders that we are still here, and the pain didn't destroy us forever. reminders that we didn't let the wound have the last word. we fought for our self in the aftermath. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the mending, the streams of gold bringing all the broken parts together, tell the story of how we fought for our self, for our heart. they are beautiful symbols of the strength, perseverance, self-love, hope, and so much more we have demonstrated by embracing our broken pieces.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

guaidó is attempting to fire the directors of citgo petroleum, which is owned by venezuela’s state oil company pdvsa, and seeks to appoint his own new board.

text:
📌 короткая, но очень примечательная статья в газете the new york times относительно движения #metoo. самый характерный - последний абзац о том, как компании отреагировали на задачу снизить риск сексуального домогательства, в любой из его форм: просто рекомендовали мужчинам-руководителям как можно меньше встречаться один-на-один с женщинами-подчиненными. т.е. меньше встреч - меньше риск домогательств... или ноль встреч - ноль риска... к чему это приводит, помимо очевидно меньшего риска сексуального мискондакта? ...ответ: женщины фактически выключаются из процесса наставничества и карьерного роста... #metoo это борьба женщин за свои права, а с другой стороны, проблема управления значительными рисками для современных мужчин. и у мужчин надежный ответ будет один: выкл. невольно задумаешься... или нет?
...
...

text:
*inec approves 144 observers for polls, u.s. not supporting any candidate*
.
.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the independent national electoral commission (inec) yesterday announced the names of 144 observers that will monitor the 2019 general elections.
inec, however, threatened to cancel and withdraw the accreditation of any organisation if its members or agents breach the code of conduct.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the commission, in a notice on its website, warned that any unaccredited group found in any state for the elections would be handed over to law enforcement agencies.
meanwhile, the united states of america has again cautioned against violence, saying election is not war.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the american government also stated that it is not supporting any presidential candidate.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the u.s. consul general, john braide, stated this yesterday, when he spoke at a ‘vote not fight’ sensitization campaign peace concert organized by media awareness and justice initiative (maji), held in port harcourt, rivers state.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“we are not here (in nigeria) to support any candidate. we are here to support free, fair, credible and transparent election in nigeria. election is not war.”
what's your say on this? .
.
.
.
 #nigeria #moralinstruction #youth #youthgoals #youthempowerment #youthservice #nysc #speakup # change #changemakers #metoo #voice #d2dyouthspeak #dare2dreamng

text: listen here. you're gonna have setbacks, mistakes, hiccups, and off days while you're fine tuning your masterpiece. shoot... these eyes of mine keep giving me glaring red, itchy, inflamed and watery signs to open up and see things clearly. i'm back in my hometown and blessed to have family and friends that get me and let me poke and prod them for information to make sense of gaps i've had in my life because of cptsd and other related effects to traumas in my past. i'm honored that my mother will sit and listen to me reliving traumas she has been witness to and desparately helpless in at times. through my storytelling she is triggered, yet now has the tools i've shared with her to do her own healing. and so we heal together. you see those bumps in your road, those painful memories and tragedies your faced, if you were blessed with family and friends they also lived that pain for you in their own way. so this healing i hold space with isn't just for me, it's for the ones i love and love me even if they don't do anything but witness the unfolding of the healing for we are all connected. if you or your loved ones are going through or have been through something heavy ask me if there's anything i know of that can support you on your journey of healing i'mhappy to share. if i don't know i'll find someone that does. we're in this thing called life and love together. start there.

text:
men scared of women post #metoo need to be educated not cancelled
#
it might be satisfying to joke about cancelling all white men and how all men are trash, but it doesn’t achieve anything (picture: ella byworth/metro.co.uk)according to the new york times, high powered men are avoiding working with young women because post #metoo, they’re scared. as a feminist, my initial instinct is we should solve this by putting all the rich white men on some kind of an island, like a leper colony for sexism. and according to the reaction online to the nyt article, i’m not alone. but here’s the thing: i am never going to get my leper colony. it might be satisfying to joke about cancelling all white men and how all men are trash, but it doesn’t achieve anything. rightly or wrongly (it’s the latter) men are frightened of being accused of inappropriate behaviour by women. and while people like me can shout ‘behave appropriately in the work place and everything will be fine’ until we’re blue in the face, it’s not getting us anywhere. when it came out that mike pence never spends time alone with any woman who isn’t his wife, we all rolled on the floor laughing. post #metoo, how many men are secretly following…

text: i was worried this film might be unpleasant, enraging, or difficult to watch - and parts of it were, for sure - but it was also inspirational, empowering, and satisfying. untouchable, ursula macfarlane’s exploratory documentary about media mogul harvey weinstein’s rise, and fall, gives some history into miramax and what went on internally, but focuses primarily on genuine and heartfelt testimony from several of the women who came forward and were brave enough to say yes to being filmed - some of them you know of already, some you don’t. this film honors them. the filmmakers very intentionally gave them the time and space to speak. their long pauses were unedited, heightening the emotional impact, and their faces often filled the whole screen, with them looking directly at the viewer. at times the silence was heavy in the theater, and we could hear them swallow or their lips part as we hung on their next word. this intensity was softened by beautiful geographic aerial photography - seemingly there to give us a break, i felt. during the q&a following (thank you, @ursulapics - everyone with a film at sundance should take the time to come to slc!) there was a standing ovation, and some of my takeaway (besides the fact that rosanna arquette is my new role model) is that #metoo cannot just be that thing that went viral in 2017. it was originally created in 2006. it must go on. we must have open dialogues. with each other. with men. with coworkers. with our sons. solidarity, truth, and working together is the way to let truth win over power. #untouchable #metoo #sundance2019 #womeninfilm

text:
let’s talk about sexual and domestic violence: 
let’s change the current system, men need to have the courage to stand up and question domestic violence, sexual violence, coercive behaviour and abuse. sexual violence is not a women’s issue, let’s not focus on the fact jill was beaten or jill was raped.. let’s focus on the perpetrators and why they are acting in this way. let’s challenge everyday sexism, misogyny and abuse. let’s take the status away from people who think it’s cool or funny to be derogatory about others, who victim blame or treat women or others in a lesser way. 
asking questions about jill is not going get us anywhere about preventing violence, the questions need to focus on the perpetrators, we should be asking questions about jack.. yes i understand that men are also victims, but mainly this is caused by other men. and yes i understand that women can be perpetrators. but let’s focus on a societal shift, challenging and changing behaviour so that we will not be bystanders in violence and abuse. 
also here is a link to an upcoming sexual violence exhibition at @uniofleicester which i would highly recommend attending  https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/lets-talk-about-sexual-violence-guided-tours-tickets-53293648738 
#sexualviolence #itsnotok #toxicmasculinity #universityofleicester #uol #domesticviolence #victimblaming #activisim #feminism #endsexualviolence #endmisogyny #genderviolence  #metoo

text:
in light of the super bowl activities occurring this week, we are dedicating our week to child sex trafficking prevention and awareness. if you are in or around the metro atlanta region, we need you to be on the lookout for possible child sex trafficking victims. this includes in and around local hotels and motels, as well as truck stops and residential neighborhoods. did you know that truck stops are prime locations for sex trafficking? they not only serve as the "business location" for traffickers, but they are also the transfer point for victims to be moved from one state or country to another. also, residential properties are in heavy rotation as well because they draw less attention than hotels and motels. so be on the lookout for random cars pulling up with underage kids. also, take note of an increase in random visitors entering a home in your neighborhood.rental services such as air bnb make it easier for traffickers to set up shop without being detected. and, while sex trafficking in atlanta isn't a new issue, there will be an increase in activity this week since there will be an onslaught of visitors in the area for the super bowl festivities. please keep your eyes open!! if you are a victim or suspect that a child may be a victim of human trafficking, please call 911 or call the national human trafficking resource center at 1-888-373-7888 for help. all victims of slavery and human trafficking have rights and are protected by international, federal, and state law. 
the hotline is: (1) anonymous and confidential; (2) available 24 hours a day, seven days a week; (3) able to provide help, referral to services, training, and general information; (4) accessible in 170 languages; (5) operated by a nonprofit, nongovernmental organization; and (6) toll free. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist  #super bowl 📸: @consultingexp fb page

in light of the super bowl activities occurring this week, we are dedicating our week to child sex trafficking prevention and awareness. if you are in or around the metro atlanta region, we need you to be on the lookout for possible child sex trafficking victims. this includes in and around local hotels and motels, as well as truck stops and residential neighborhoods. did you know that truck stops are prime locations for sex trafficking? they not only serve as the "business location" for traffickers, but they are also the transfer point for victims to be moved from one state or country to another. also, residential propeies are in heavy rotation as well because they draw less attention than hotels and motels. so be on the lookout for random cars pulling up with underage kids. also, take note of an increase in random visitors entering a home in your neighborhood.rental services such as air bnb make it easier for traffickers to set up shop without being detected. and, while sex trafficking in atlanta is not a new issue, there will be an increase in activity this week since there will be an onslaught of visitors in the area for the super bowl festivities. please keep your eyes open!! if you are a victim or suspect that a child may be a victim of human trafficking, please call 911 or call the national human trafficking resource center at 1-888-373-7888 for help. all victims of slavery and human trafficking have rights and are protected by international, federal, and state law.

text:
tarana burke. if you don't recognize her name or face, you will know her by her work. @taranajaneen is the founder of the #metoo movement. this badass women was named one of the "silence breakers" for how she broke the silence of sexual assault, sexual violence, and rape. of course, she couldn't have done it if thousands of men and women weren't willing to share their testimony of their past. this ground breaking movement opened america's eyes as to just how common this epidemic really is. 
if that wasn't enough, she also founded the just be inc. which helps promote wellness in young minority girls during the pivotal age between 12-18. she also had a large role in the #survivingrkelly docu-series. if you haven't watched that series, you should but it's a huge **trigger warning**
so thank you, tarana burke for being such a badass, and giving survivors, and young minority women a place where they can speak up, and feel safe! we need more people like her, now more than ever.

text:
¡hola, querubines! 👼🏻👼🏼👼🏾
estoy muy emocionada porque después de pasar de digital a papel aquí en españa, oh my gothess cruza el atlántico para desembarcar en latinoamérica.🛫
📌
¿cuándo y dónde? 
enero: méxico.
febrero: argentina.
gracias a @dnxspain y @delnuevoextremo por hacerlo posible.
😍
¡mis feelings!
la noticia me hace especial ilusión, ya que cuando empezaba en mi aventura literaria conocí a gente maravillosa de la que me separan muchos kilómetros, pero a la que me sentía próxima después de horas de conversación.
tengo ganas de ver fotos de #ohmygothess
en vuestras manos y estanterías, de sentir su viaje como algo real, un viaje del que sois parte gracias al cariño que le dais a nessa, isaac y su historia.
gracias por estar al otro lado: de la pantalla, del libro, del océano.💖
vuestro apoyo lo es todo para mí.
❓
dudas everywhere...
¿podrá conseguirse en más países de latinoamérica? por supuesto, pero soy cauta y de momento os digo lo que sé con total seguridad. 
si vivís en otro lugar y queréis saber si hay distribución de omg en vuestra zona, no dudéis en preguntar a del nuevo extremo.
ℹ
distribución en méxico: @oceanomexico
distribución en argentina: @oceano_argentina
.
.

text:
feminism. is it necessary?
i'm @theexpater and i had this conversation with someone recently. they argued that feminism and especially the #metoo movement has become a trend, a fad, along with avo on toast and millennial unicorns.
seriously?!
sure, on the whole, feminism is now no longer a dirty word. amen to that.
sure, in parts of the world women enjoy much greater freedoms than their grandmothers could even dream of. 
but that's not to say we're there now.
most recently uae announced its equality awards, which were won by... wait for it... drum roll... men. all awards were won by men.
and what about the pay gap around the globe? in the us on average women earn 80% of a man's salary. 
for me at least, feminism may have shifted its focus, but it's as relevant and crucial as ever.

thank goodness for organisations like @aauwnational, @awidwomensrights
@timesupnow & @weareultraviolet 
what do you think? who are your feminist heroes?  #unitedinwomanhood
thank you 📷 @arielebonte

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
close-up... see on the side of my face... yes.. i have a beard... the saloon guy told me have a threading done.. stupid fellow can shave his face but i have get a threading done and see hell in pain... i'm gonna keep the beard for now... not worth going through the pain.  getting rid of the upper lip moustache itself is painful enough. . 
fyi.. i have never got my eyebrows done.. i don't get the point...
i mean they are there for what joy? does anyone know the functions of eye brows?

text:
holding on! 
i am holding on to my blanket... i am suffering from severe pms as i am due and over an above i ate something stupid and landed with a stomach upset. .
the flash is on because i am in my room in the dark.. i am not confident enough to put on a face with no smile. a swollen,  kajal smudged face is what i have right now with messy hair.. the tear drops fall on my phone making it so hard to type as the letters go ffffdff and i have to wipe it with my shirt every 30 secs to get the tears off.
i had therapy today and i was alright...
the downfall was pretty rapid.... this is the life of a bipolar! 
worse being a girl whose menses cycles are in tact... #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #metoo  #loneliness #pain #despair #prettygirls #perfectbody #hurtquotes #goodenough #positivevibes

text:
i tell my story not because it is unique. it’s not, it is the story of many girls. -

when you can finally tell it and not cry, you know you have healed #timesup
- 📸 and ✍️ by @graceandshinephoto -

we see stories of strangers, of co workers forcing themselves upon another. but remember those who are close members in personal life, target too. when it happens you have no idea if it was wrong or “okay.” you’re left confused and in a daze and ignore its effect calling it “normal” or “he just didn’t know.” no means no. teach our girls to understand that and empower them while teaching our boys to respect it by example.- @timesupnow #timesupnow #metoo 
it’s monday! and this is my silly face of crazy crunch time, work, and being a mom. i sometimes have no idea how i do it. but i know part is because i have some rocks in my life. pebbles will come and leave and rocks are there to stay. -

text:
🚨 alert! 🚨⠀
there are only 3️⃣ days left to tell @betsydevosed to keep her #handsoffix.⠀
⠀
the proposed rule states that, “at any time prior to reaching a determination regarding responsibility the recipient may facilitate an informal resolution process, such as mediation, that does not involve a full investigation and adjudication.” if students choose an informal resolution, such as mediation, they cannot, at any point, return to a formal adjudication process, thus trapping them in a process that may not have their best interest at heart.⠀
⠀
mediation does not require individuals to take responsibility for the harm that they have caused prior to participation in an informal resolution proceeding. as a result, facilitators engaged in a mediation proceeding (as opposed to restorative justice), may engage in conduct implying that survivors and perpetrators are equally at fault for experiences of intimate partner or acquaintance violence. moreover, schools have monetary and reputational incentives to downplay claims of violence and harassment, and in some cases have ave pressured survivors to participate in informal mediations.⠀
⠀
make your voice heard by submitting your comment today. 📣 handsoffix.org ➡️ link in bio. ⠀

🇫🇷 coucou,
un extrait du recueil #desauteursautoeditessemobilisentcontreleharcelementderue que vous pouvez retrouver avec d’autres sur @booknode 👍
il s’agit de la nouvelle « entrez dans la ronde » de guillaume marin 😊
en tout, 17 nouvelles et donc 17 voix pour s’exprimer sur le harcèlement dans les lieux publics envers des femmes, des couples homosexuels, des victimes du racisme, etc.
des genres et des tons différents.
il est en vente aux formats papier et ebook 📚
un immense merci à @lmedml.alouqua qui vous propose aussi un rdv chronique + interview sur son blog chaque mardi 😉
bonne journée 🌤
•••
📒 vous pouvez retrouver mes livres, les ajouter à votre pal et consulter des extraits sur les sites de lecture comme babelio, livraddict, booknode et goodreads à mon nom d’autrice s. n. lemoing 😊
🛍 ils sont disponibles gratuitement en emprunt avec amazon kindle ou à 2.99€ pour les romans et 0.99€ pour les histoires courtes au format ebook, et entre 8 et 11€ pour les versions papier 📖
•••
🇬🇧 hi,
an excerpt from a short story of the anthology about street harassment!
this novella is about several characters who don’t realize they harass people. reading it shows us we can have inappropriate behavior, we should be careful how we treat others!
there’s a facebook page for the book. 17 novellas have been selected, 17 voices for women, queer people, people of color, etc. who have been harassed.
have a great time 🌤
•••
📚 if you love epic fantasy & badass female characters you can read more info about my writings in my bio. one of them has been acclaimed by 100+ literary bloggers 😊
🛍 my writings are available for free for kindle unlimited subscribers, as ebooks at 1,15$ or 0,99£, etc. & paperback for $14 👍

des genres et des tons différents.

an excerpt from a sho story of the anthology about street harassment!
this novella is about several characters who don’t realize they harass people. reading it shows us we can have inappropriate behavior, we should be careful how we treat others!
there’s a facebook page for the book. 17 novellas have been selected, 17 voices for women, queer people, people of color, etc. who have been harassed.
have a great time 🌤

text: so i guess this is part of my problem. i am anxious, upset and frozen for 2 days where i lay in bed and do the bare minimum of work i have to do to keep up with clients. then he comes back picks a fight to try and justify why he left. there is travel for work so we leave town and he acts like nothing happens but of course some shady moments while we are away. if you could only imagine what is said and why all this is happening. i know deep in my heart this is not my fault. i know that when someone shames you and says this is all your fault and this is happening because you are fat cannot be true. maybe true for him. if you saw me walking down the street you wouldn’t notice me. i don’t stand out as skinny or fat or anything. am i and athlete shape, no! could i lose another 20 to 30 lbs yes i can and it’s been a constant struggle my whole life. but i exercise regularly and my biggest challenge in life is to eat properly and take care of myself. i started this post about 3 weeks ago but have been so busy working i never finished. it does say something about consistency and something i struggle with but work has been so much it was all i could handle. #metoo #codependency #recovery #ithastogetbetter #workhard #mentalhealth #secrets #lies
