text: see what people are saying about candy apple butterscotch, #newauthor rebecca macceile’s debut publication. “this is an impactful read if you have ever experienced any sort of abuse. i appreciate the author’s candor and willingness to write with such openness. she takes responsibility for herself as much as she describes the lasting effects of trauma.” “it is worth the read. it’s about a woman empowered and, my god, that is a wonderful thing indeed.” “the author gets to the point while still painting a very clear and definite picture for the readers and i love that. the accounts of the trauma are laid out in such a way that you know what’s happening and are able to imagine it but you aren’t bombarded with intense graphic imagery, which i appreciate as a survivor myself. would definitely recommend!” “this amazingly written gem takes you inside the author’s world and keeps you there, making you feel like a discreet “bug on the wall.” i could not put it down.” “i wish everyone would write a memoir. it would be so much easier to understand people. i haven’t been through anything as violent or traumatic, but i think this story is relatable in a lot of ways. it just makes me see a lot of things differently in every day life. it’s a big eye opener.” #onsalenow at the #linkinbio. #kindle and #paperback versions available! also for members of #amazonprime, candy apple butterscotch is available in the #kindlelendinglibrary as well as through #kindleunlimitedbooks! that’s right you can read for #free. #nonfictionbooks #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor #kindlestoryteller2018  #kindledirectpublishing #onsalenow #paperback #kindlelendinglibrary #bookrecommendations #indieauthor #authorsofinstagram #amazon #readforfreekll

text:
*ya sabes como bajamos!* *pero te preguntaste como subimos?*🛩 la respuesta es:
*cessna 205*. este maravilloso pájaro d acero forma parte de una familia de aeronaves monomotor de propósito general, usados en servicios comerciales como en la aviación privada. también son conocidos como super skywagon, stationair o super skylane. esos modelos más populares dentro de los aviones se unen una construcción robusta y una cabina grande con un motor potente. es considerada una de las mejores aeronaves para skydive y en fotografía aérea.

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ 이 프로젝트는 사진가 이종혁 작가님과 함께 합니다. 그는 주변에서 일어난 일련의 사건을 통해 피해자의 정신적 스트레스와 고통을 통감하며 이번 프로젝트를 위해 그의 작품을 기부했습니다. 이종혁 작가의 작품 'vivid dream' (2018)은 열정을 갖고 살아가면 예상치 못한 불행이 닥치더라도 이를 극복하고, 희망찬 미래를 맞이할 수 있다는 의미를 담고 있습니다. 그의 작품 속에 고스란히 담겨있는 붉은 열정과 푸른 미래가 여러분께도 전달되길 바랍니다.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀ * 작품 후면에  작가님 사인과 에디션 넘버링이 들어가요! ⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
'태양이 서산으로 기울기 시작한 어느 날,
문득 올려다본 하늘입니다. 먹구름 사이로 보이는 흰 구름은 해 질 녘 태양빛을 받아 붉게 물들었고, 그 사이로 어렴풋이 푸른 하늘이 보였습니다.
그날은 유독 힘이 들었는지 일상의 풍경이 낯설더군요.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
붉은 열정이 검은 불행을 밀어내고 푸른 미래를 맞이하려는 듯한 풍경이 마치 우리네 인생을 한 장의 사진으로 보는 것 같달까요?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
어렴풋이 내비치던 푸른 하늘은 이후에 얼마나 더 또렷해졌을까요?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
누구에게나 똑같이 펼쳐져 있는 하늘입니다.
모두가 푸른 하늘 위를 자유롭게 날아다니길 꿈꿔봅니다.'
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

- 작품명: vivid dream
- 연도: 2018
- 작가명: 이종혁
- 작품크기: 6x9inch (15.3 x 22.9cm)
- 소재: 디아섹 우드 프레임
- 에디션: limited edition number/300
- 사인: 작품 후면 작가 사인 및 에디션 넘버링
- 가격: 70,000원
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
*300개 한정 작품입니다. 작품은 디아섹 우드 프레임으로 제작되어 탁상형 혹은 벽걸이로 겸할 수 있습니다.
배송은 주문 후 약 3일이 소요됩니다.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
작품 판매 수익금 중 일부는 '한국 성폭력 상담소'에 기부하여 성희롱 근절 캠페인 및 직장 내 성희롱 예방교육에 뜻깊게 사용될 예정입니다. 단순히 일회성의 이벤트가 아닌 지속적인 관심과 후원이 필요하다고 생각합니다. 많은 분들의 참여 부탁드립니다.

text:
저는 여전히 두렵고 무섭습니다. 좋은 뜻으로 시작한 일이 저의 발목을 붙잡을 수도 있겠다 싶습니다. 제가 당한 일은 매우 작고, 아무것도 아닌 일로 치부되었습니다. '사회생활 하다보면 그럴 수도 있지' 라며.. 작은 일을 굳이 크게 만들 필요 있겠냐며 저를 회유하는 목소리도 적지 않았습니다. 
누군가가 널 만진 것도 아니고, 고작 전화 너머로 욕설과 폭언, 여성 성기를 지칭하는 단어를 쓴 것을 가지고 너무 심하게 피해의식을 느끼는 것 아니냐며 오히려 저를 이상한 사람 취급한 분도 있었죠. 그게 일반적인 생각일지도 모릅니다. 
저 스스로도 제가 너무 예민해서 참지 못하는 걸 수도 있다며 잘못된 생각을 했었습니다. 당연히 그런일 쯤은 참고 견뎌야 한다 스스로를 다그쳤죠. 그러나 저를 응원해주고 지지해주는 많은 분들께 보여드리고 싶습니다. 잘못된 것은 바로잡을 수 있으며, 용기를 낼 수록 그 힘은 커진다는 것을요.

text: this is my monday motivation (there is hope)i am proof there is such a thing as ‘trauma drama’ i lived in it for years, and it was endless amounts of suffering, my own personal hell. at the time i didn’t understand i was doing it to myself, no one but myself could end my suffering. countless triggers, debilitating fear and hopelessness.  i had to teach myself to let it go.  it takes practice, patience and self compassion. but change is possible. if you are reading this there is hope.  you were harmed which is outside of your control, and it likely changed the way you view the world. you don’t deserve to continue to suffer you deserve peace and happiness and it is possible the way you view the world and yourself can change💞#journey2soulful #hope #peace #happiness #ptsd #recovery #spiritualawakening #pain #suffering #changethewayyouviewtheworld #selflove #selfcompassion #thejourneyisworthit #letitgo #lifequotes #quotestoliveby #quoteoftheday #motivationmonday #happymonday #youdidnothingwrong #metoo #bewhoyouweremeanttobe #inspire #change #love #life #wordswagapp

text:
as lilia tarawa describes her life in a cult, i found it so eerily familiar.  i realize the techniques that her grandfather (the leader of the cult) and her community used to brainwash and break her down were the same the same as my ex mother in law and her family.

1. shame and humiliate you in front of others. she would tell me i'm too fat, too outspoken, etc.

2. use the community to reinforce this belief that you're the problem. my ex husband's identical twin (paul tsai) and her husband, din tsai, have said her beating me is justified because i'm the problem.

3. make you believe that you're unworthy of love. she would ask me regularly what i did for her son. then she would praise her sons in front of me and tell me how lucky i am to be with her son.

today, like lilia tarawa, i break the chains of this abuse because of my love for my son.

it wasn't until i watched this video (https://tinyurl.com/ydymh57w) that i realize that i couldn't write my book 3 years ago because i hadn't learned the greatest lesson yet - self love.

and that is why i'm so proud to finally come to a title that fully encompasses my journey, "belonging: self love lessons from a workaholic depressed insomniac lawyer." if you have been in an abusive relation - emotional, verbal, or physical - know that you are worthy of love.

leaving may be difficult.  but happiness is possible.

#selflove #speakupshoutout #womenmatter #metoo

text:
#excelncia !
servicio de excelente calidad. calificado por quienes ya han experimentado con nosotros que se siente tocar el cielo con las manos!

el certificado de excelencia de tripadvisor rinde homenaje a determinados alojamientos, atracciones y restaurantes que demuestran constantemente un compromiso de excelencia en la hospitalidad.

para determinar a los ganadores del certificado de excelencia, tripadvisor utiliza un algoritmo de su propiedad que tiene en cuenta la cantidad, la calidad y la actualidad de las opiniones y comentarios que envían los viajeros de tripadvisor en un periodo de 12 meses, al igual que la antigüedad del negocio y su clasificación en el índice de popularidad en el sitio. para calificar para un certificado de excelencia, un negocio debe mantener una calificación general de al menos cuatro de cinco burbujas en tripadvisor, tener una cantidad de mínima de opiniones y haber tenido el perfil en tripadvisor por al menos 12 meses.

text:
abuela radical: conoce la señora que ha saltado en paracaídas a los 103 años

seguro que ya oíste que nunca es tarde para realizar un sueño, o que es posible escribir una nueva historia o comenzar de cero. mientras tenemos vida, somos capaces de actuar de forma fantástica y sorprendente. pensando en eso, resolvimos contar la encantadora historia de una persona super valiente, que pasó por skydivefoz para realizar el sueño de saltar en paracaídas.

nuestra fuente de inspiración de hoy es doña aida mendes, o mejor, la querida doña iaiá – la famosa señora que realizó un salto en paracaídas a los 103 años de edad en skydivefoz. amante del deporte y con ganas de desafíos, abuela iaiá es un ejemplo de serenidad y buena onda. mira más sobre su historia:

https://youtu.be/okipfrxnd8g

text:
con salud de sobra, doña aida – nacida en 1909– tiene mucha energía positiva y es adepta de varios deportes: caminatas, trote, natación, fútbol y mucho más. a pesar de la avanzada edad, ella está siempre en movimiento y en busca de cosas nuevas.

en 2013, con el apoyo de su familia y amigos, se puso a romper el récord mundial y saltó en skydivefoz, mostrando un poquito de su vitalidad y coraje. ella entró para la historia y batió el récord de persona más vieja a saltar en paracaídas.

doña iaiá añadió el deporte a su lista de favoritos y actualmente realiza diversos saltos en paracaídas en brasil. siempre muy calma y con paz en la mirada, aida mendes es inspiración para personas de todas las edades.

text:
salto en paracaídas para todas las edades

el salto tándem puede ser hecho por personas de prácticamente todas las edades. apenas menores de 16 años no pueden saltar y, con hasta 18, es necesario presentar una autorización de los responsables.

a muchas personas le da miedo la altura y acaban por desistir del salto, pero la seguridad del equipo, y profesionalismo de los instructores garantiza una experiencia inolvidable y 100% segura. doña iaiá pudo comprobarlo al saltar, y entró en nuestra lista, que cuenta con más de 20.000 saltos realizados.

si el salto en paracaídas también hace parte de tus sueños, es bueno que conozcas más sobre, para enfrentar este gran desafío. la vista espectacular, la adrenalina y sensación de libertad son algunas de las cosas que ayudan a enfrentar la altitud.

text:
@amazon announced this week that they are in the process of creating an app that would allow its customers to try on their outfits in the virtual world. the app would scour a customer's social media photographs to predict their fashion style before identifying possible suggestions, in the style of the 1995 movie clueless. using algorithms from a person’s personal information, the app would predict their preferred outfit choice, then place its predicted outfit on a virtual mannequin. 💁🏽‍♀️
new blog post up on how technology is quickly wiping out modelling - how 3d models, holographs and algorithms are being used instead of fashion models. is this the end of exploitation? not yet - many models are unknowingly being used as the prototype for these programs taking their jobs and don’t even know about it! whilst rates are falling, the profit models are making for businesses is rising more than ever with new ways of marketing such as live purchases off a catwalk show. check the blog to find out how to protect yourself against the robots and keep up to date with the latest tech changing the industry beyond recognition.
name: The Model Manifesto

text:
we are infinitely happy to have yuko shimizu @yukoart as our next lw&d interview.  originally from tokyo and now based in new york, yuko is a freelance illustrator and instructor at the school of visual arts. illustration is actually yuko’s second career. she says, “i have an undergraduate degree in business (advertising and marketing), and had a corporate pr career in japan for 11 years before i quit, moved to ny, and enrolled myself in sva to start a new career path… i always loved to draw, and getting a stable corporate job never made me happy. around the age of 30, i stopped and thought about whether it was really something i wanted to keep doing. the answer was no. so from there, i went soul searching, then made up my mind to try myself out in art. worked a few years more to save up enough money to move to ny and pay for four years of art school… and here i am!” her advice to other creatives: “i can’t speak for other industries, but as a freelance illustrator mainly working in editorial, book and ad markets, i can’t stress enough: none of my clients ever care if you are a woman, or a man, young or old, an american or not, minority or not, if you have phd or dropped out of high school… you are only judged by the images you create, and that is really really liberating and a fantastic field to be working in.” yuko shimizu’s full interview is on our lw&d website listed in our profile above. #ladieswinedesign #yukoshimizu ✨🙌💥
.
.
.

text:
良き人生には、3つの要素がある。
学ぶこと、稼ぐこと、
そしてあくびをすること。

頑張ることはすごいことだ。
頑張り続けるのはもっとすごいことだ。
稼ぐということはすごいことだ。
稼ぐということは、世の中に価値を与えているということだ。

でも、それをひたすらにやり続けること、きっと誰にもできやしない。
進み続けて、疲れたら休んだら良い。
立ち止まって考えることで、新しい道が見えてくる。

text:
hello everyone,
angela christofilou (@angela_photographs / @protests_photos) here taking over insta for this week. 
i've been building an archive of protest photography for the past few years so i'll be mainly posting various images from these for this take-over.
the image in the intro poster was taken during a @sistersuncut march in nov 2015. trafalgar square's fountains were dyed red to resemble the blood of women killed by domestic violence. "they cut, we bleed"
in this post, i have featured a photo i shot at the women's march in london. 
thanks to @photo_scratch for having me and for your time.
#womensmarch #london #sistersuncut #metoo #documentaryphotography #photojournalism #portrait #protest #photoscratch #angelachristofilou #londonphotocommunity #photonetwork #blackandwhite #streetphotography #shotoncanon

text:
sexual harassment

do not stand for it
do not brush it off 
it’s a disgraceful truth as you go on to acquiring more experiences in life that u as a woman are subjected to harassment. doesn’t matter how smart, ambitious, or professional u are & most importantly how u look like or what u wear. 
i, like most women out there have been subjected to countless of situations & fallen victim to prey.it’s demeaning & violating. 
r these type of men really so incapable of fighting their “primal” instincts? i can’t comprehend this innate desire to be perceived as animals #vegans is this insulting? perhaps. i’ve never encountered an animal sexually harassing anyone so i’m out of description methods.

calling out all those hiding behind their suits, beards & titles.who think it’s ok for a woman to have to wake up every morning & dread the day’s possible evolvement

how will she be disgraced today? 
used to close deals?hired for her appearance rather than capabilities?how about the predator manager who physically sexually harasses her?offices that put up cameras meant for security reasons but rather used by a perverted senior to monitor her?

the saddest part to most of such stories are the people u share them with;more often than not the first questions are:
what do u wear?
how do u talk?
well, i’m in no way provocative in neither speech nor clothing. 
it infuriates me that justification of bad behavior is looked for. predators don’t need a reason.

the office is a place for productivity & development in whichever field, a place to contribute positively to society, it’s a responsibility & sets a preset for the coming generations.

i believe all communities, men & women have a responsibility to set in motion preventative measures.  a responsibility to form teachings embedded in the mind to create environments which are enabling not disabling.

i hope anybody who reads this takes action for themselves & others, i hope u don’t feel alone, embarrassed or silenced. i hope your voice is heard & your head is held high clothed in strength & pride. proud to be a woman, a precious creation, soul & body with infinite capabilities. don’t let anybody stand in the way of your magic.

text:
мы давно мечтаем подготовить емкий материал на тему лгбт-сообщества в городе, но боимся, что со спикерами могут возникнуть некоторые сложности. ведь непросто позвонить так знакомым и попросить рассказать, как там у них в мире все работает: знакомства, браки, суррогатное материнство, в конце концов.
⠀
каминг-аут в провинции почти исключен, как и всякое другое #metoo, но слухами полнится земля: про кого-то говорят уверенно, кто-то вызывает сомнения. бесспорно одно: в этом городе все неровно дышат к чужому интиму, особенно если он чем-то отличается от привычного домашнего стандарта.
⠀
с другой стороны, окна овертона открываются все шире, и, кажется, что все это — личное дело человека, и все в полном порядке. наш глянцевый мир тем более чуть ли не продюсирует свободный и open-minded образ жизни.
⠀
давайте хотя бы в соцсетях про это поговорим, какое у вас мнение по лгбт-вопросу?

text:
i wrote “girls suck” in sharpie on my high school deck ‘cause i was confused about my gender and frustrated at how to fit in with the presented “options” for how girls / women “should be” required such disempowerment and sameness ... it just didn’t work for me at all #90s #riotgrrrl #feminist
.
i also had deep unconscious fear of women / women in authority positions due to emotional & psychological abuse #gaslighting from my mother #cptsd and inappropriate touch from a gymnastics coach before the 5th grade
.
becoming “one of the boys” helped me hide from my own cis-gender identity crisis by adopting the behaviors and dress of the #punk and #skater boys i hung around and felt the most comfortable with
.
“if i’m one of the boys, then i will be safe from sexual assault / being harassed”
.
or, so i thought ... despite wearing clothes that mostly hid my body & staying skinny (underdeveloped) as a three sport athlete, i still got my crotch & barely there breasts grabbed at punk shows crowd-surfing & in mosh pits
.
later in life, that “one of the boys” false protection mechanism took the form of being overly logical / analytical in the workplace & denying my feelings, drinking “with the guys” shot-for-shot at happy hours, and building my body into a muscled, more “masculine” shape via #crossfit for 7 years
.
there’s so much more to unpack here & write about ... just sharing a bit now as in real-time i am feeling such gratitude for the healing work i’ve done to define, create & embody my own sense of #gender #sexuality #female #feminine w empowered, grounded, mystical, rich earth-mother #empress #divinefeminine energy vs. market #stereotypes
.
and i am proud of the progress i’ve made in healing my relationship to my mother, and from the sexual assault of my younger years & being raped a few years ago #metoo #timesup
.
it is wonderful to feel safe in my own skin, and to love all of it, curves and all without fear ... to know my power comes from within and doesn’t have a damn thing to do with what i wear, how i ride, or what anyone else thinks about how i “present” my gender or sexuality
.
the body is merely a #meatsuit for the soul’s expression anyway ... con’t 👇🏼

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for adveising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robe mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

.
🌴идеальные месяцы для посещение марокко - это с марта по начало мая и с конца сентября по ноябрь , хотя я была в декабре погода была отличная , правда ночи очень холодные 😬 температура днем + 20-25 , ночью + 7 -9 , имейте в виду , что с мая по сентябрь - это +40 , а в пустыне все + 50 .
🌴из вещей я бы посоветовала взять длинные легкие платья , панамы, кроссовки, сандальи , теплую кофту . как одеваться в  марокко , конечно тема отдельная 😉 .
🌴передвигаться лучше всего на машине , так возможно увидеть больше красивых мест и конечно сделать красивые фото .
🌴 что косается жилья , то тут конечно первое место занимают роскошные риады, в них вы почувствуете все обоняние марокко, в однотипных отелях можно пожить и в других странах .😛
🌴деньги лучше сразу обменять на дирхамы и лучше всего здесь меняют с евро . .
🌴из еды обязательно нужно попробывать тажин , свеже приготовленную рыбу и устриц  которую только, что выловили в океане , ореховую эмлю (это моя любовь😍) которую также готовят при вас на базарах , мандарины и конечно выпить литры апельсинового сока . .
🌴из развлечений для меня это базар и сёрфинг , а еще можно поваляться на пляже . конечно , можно сходить и в ночной клуб , но будьте готовы алкоголь встречается редко. .
🌴дела с интернетом , тоже хорошо , ловит практически везде , я купила местную симку с тарифом 15 g , за 700р .
☝️ну и главный совет , если хотите увидеть страну и уехать  с хорошими воспоминаниями обратитесь к гиду , вы с экономите кучу денег и нервов. .
кому нужна помощь обращайтесь , буду рада помочь 😀🌴
.
.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with ficial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

.

text:
.........victim blaming .........
.
.
if you have not been sexually assaulted or experienced sexual harassment then you won't understand how painful victim-blaming can be.
.
.
 survivors are often asked what they were wearing, what they did to “encourage” the perpetrator, or even why they didn’t fight back more.
.
.
with the #metoo movement, victim-blaming remains a tenacious problem.
.
.
the tendency to blame the victim may be part of society's conditioning. .
.
ask yourself would any woman intentionally put themselves in a position to be abused? 
victim-blaming doesn’t have to involve accusing survivors of directly causing their own misfortune. .
.
it could be as simply asking the question "why did you stay"?
or what were you wearing?
.
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
hurt a poet and she’ll make you her poetry.
she won’t name you, worry not,
but you’ll itch and write at the lament,
even if you claim you’re made of diamonds.
.
leave a poet and she’ll see you in the skies,
musingly staring with the ghost of a smile,
thinking of all the words she could use
to embellish her next cathartic piece with.
.
make a poet cry and with every tear
that escapes her weary eyes,
she’ll create oceans with the currents so unfathomable
that your winds of oblivion will stir up.
.
so tear a poet apart and she’ll at once
write and write about you; exploit your evil.
come up with the most melancholic beauty
that you’ll ever read when you find someone
just like yourself.
.
and isn’t that what poets do best?
suffer pain like every other being,
only to write about it as if
writing is their salvation, and poetry, their sin.
.
.
sneha talwar.
(@issnehaaa)
.
.
.
.

text: funambulism: a poem from 10 years ago that was one of the influences of my recent painting by the same name. funambulism is the art of tightrope walking. i wrote this piece 10 years ago. it’s crazy how much changes in that time. as i appreciate my life’s ups and downs now, it’s clear that my view was very different then. i tell people all the time that positivity is something that takes practice to become second nature and determination to see during the hard times. it’s clear that i didn’t have much practice at it ten years ago. that said, i love this time capsule, shows how much i’ve learned and grown. the best part about this piece though is its structure. i’m always playing with words but this small series was extra special in its complexity. this was part of my “four poems on a page”. the challenge i created for myself in these was creating four stanzas that could stand alone. so, if you read this poem across and line by line, you get one picture. if you read this piece by its independent columns (left, middle, right), you have an additional 3 unique expressions. i also love the visual balance of the words on the page. that was very intentional, wanted it to reflect a central body with things teetering on either side as i’d imagine the experience of walking down a tightrope. it was a fun exercise that i might just revisit sometime. anyway, here’s another version of the 10 year challenge. #livingwithart #jennifire #tenyearchallenge #attitudeofgratitude #happinessishere #mondayvibes #balancedlife #mindfulness #poetry #whereicomefrom #metoo #writersofinstagram #simplelife  #womenartists #dallasart #glasslife #weareone #tightrope #oprahsbookclub #bigtop #balancingact #artlove  #womenwriters #meditation #plur #plurlife #blessup #soulshine #lovequotes #lifelesson

text:
"h e a r i n g"
definisi (noun): an opportunity to state your case and be heard.

namun, begitu sampai di ruangan dpr, terkuaklah sudah:
anggota dewan dprd yang hadirーkecuali bu agathaーjelas hadir tidak untuk mendengarkan.

mereka justru hadir untuk menyangkal,
mempertanyakan,
meragukan.
seolah-olah perempuan-perempuan yang rela menyisakan waktunyaーyang rela jauh-jauh datang dari seluruh pelosok jawa timur, bahkan dari tubanー "ujug-ujug datang" tanpa mempelajari dahulu apa itu ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual.

niat baik, katanya. ya, dengan mempertanyakan berulangkali apa yang padahal bersumber dari pengalaman hidup perempuan itu sehari-hari. 
ala-ala paternalistik, seolah dewan dprd mengetahui pengalaman hidup perempuan lebih baik daripada perempuan itu sendiri. (di sini saja kami 'lelah hayati', tidak bisa dibayangkan korban yang seusai melewati trauma, harus diinterogasi dengan pertanyaan senonoh berulang kali). apa yang terjadi di ruang dprd jawa timur ini sejatinya adalah refleksi dari bagaimana masyarakat memperlakukan penyintas kekerasan seksual: 
penyintas diragukan, 
disangkal, 
dibuat seolah "gila", dan 
dipersalahkan.

oh ya di sini lucunya: mereka meng-klaim jika pasal dari ruu ini ada yang digerogoti, ini seolah-olah karena kegagalan kita mengawal ruu ini, dan ketidakpahaman kita atas ruu ini. ini logik yang aneh. 
justru inilah tugas anda, dewan dprd, untuk mengawal ruu ini supaya ruh dan esensi dari ruu ini tidak diamputasi. anda tidak berpikir bahwa pajak kami digunakan untuk membayar anda duduk-duduk santai di ruang ber-ac, kan?

namanya saja "hearing": coba buka hati dan telinga, agar bukti-bukti, narasi, dan suara  kami tidak "masuk kuping kiri, keluar kuping kanan". ini bukan waktu bagi anda untuk bersikukuh berdasarkan apa yang menurut anda benar. justru, ini waktu untuk mengkritisi pengetahuan anda dengan pengalaman empiris perempuan yang sesungguhnya. 
anda beruntung.kapan lagi toh anda ada kesempatan untuk mendengarkan suara perempuan korban kekerasan yang selama ini dibungkam masyarakat? 【16haktp jawa timur】
【hearing dengan dprd jawa timur @ 17 dec 18】
【jaringan jawa timur pendukung pengesahan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual】

text:
#미투 #metoo 
아프기전의 이야기 그리고 미투..
나는 학창시절 소심하고 낯가림이 심해서 친구가 거의 없었다 .
.
.
방황하는 나를 안정시킨건 체육관이었다 . 운동을 좋아했고 몸쓰는것도 좋았다 .
.
.
그렇게 나의 안정감을 준 체육관에 내가 좋아하는 사람이 생겼다 .그는 잘생겼고 27살이었다.
우리는 천천히 친해졌고 , 핸드폰이 없는 나에게 쪽지를 주었다.
시간과 장소가 있고 추가적으로 붙은 말든 누구한테더 얘기하지 말고 혼자 올것 이라고 적혀있었다 .
.
.
나는 설레는 마음에 혼자 소설을 쓰며 고백받으면 어쩌지 뭐라고 말하지?? 기쁜 마음으로  계단으로 향했다. .
.
장소에 도착하니 오빠가 서있었고 왔냐며 물었고 난 수줍게 웃었다. 
그러면서 지금부터 내가 하는 행동이나 말에 너무 놀라지말라며 당부를 했다 . 난 아무렇지 않게 알겠다라고 했다.
말이 끝나기 무섭게 오빠는 바지를 벗었다 속옷도 벗었다 ..
나는 너무 놀라 아무말도 하지 못했고 오빠는 내손을 강제로 만지게 했다.
그게 끝이 아니었다. 내 가슴을 만지며 강제로 키스를 했다. 손이 나의 바지로 오려는 순간 인기척이 났고 겨우 놀란마음을 진정시키며 그자리를 뛰쳐나왔다 . 
성에 관련된건 학교에서 대충 알려줬었고 나는 정확한걸 알기에는 너무 어린 고작15살이었다.
나는 내가 멍청하다고 생각했다 .
멍청하게 당하고만 있던 내가 너무 창피하고 분했다 .
.
.
근데 이건 시작에 불과했다...
.
.

그렇게 나의 안정감을 준 체육관에 내가 좋아하는 사람이 생겼다 .그는 잘생겼고 27살이었다.
우리는 천천히 친해졌고 , 핸드폰이 없는 나에게 쪽지를 주었다.
시간과 장소가 있고 추가적으로 붙은 말든 누구한테더 얘기하지 말고 혼자 올것 이라고 적혀있었다 .
.
.
나는 설레는 마음에 혼자 소설을 쓰며 고백받으면 어쩌지 뭐라고 말하지?? 기쁜 마음으로  계단으로 향했다. .
.
장소에 도착하니 오빠가 서있었고 왔냐며 물었고 난 수줍게 웃었다. 
그러면서 지금부터 내가 하는 행동이나 말에 너무 놀라지말라며 당부를 했다 . 난 아무렇지 않게 알겠다라고 했다.
말이 끝나기 무섭게 오빠는 바지를 벗었다 속옷도 벗었다 ..
나는 너무 놀라 아무말도 하지 못했고 오빠는 내손을 강제로 만지게 했다.
그게 끝이 아니었다. 내 가슴을 만지며 강제로 키스를 했다. 손이 나의 바지로 오려는 순간 인기척이 났고 겨우 놀란마음을 진정시키며 그자리를 뛰쳐나왔다 . 
성에 관련된건 학교에서 대충 알려줬었고 나는 정확한걸 알기에는 너무 어린 고작15살이었다.
나는 내가 멍청하다고 생각했다 .
멍청하게 당하고만 있던 내가 너무 창피하고 분했다 .
.
.
근데 이건 시작에 불과했다...
.
.

#댓글읽어주는기자들 22화에서는 11년 전 폭로 되었던 믿기 힘든 #스포츠성폭력, 아직도 벌어지고 있는 이유에 대해 다뤄봅니다. (with 정재용 스포츠 기자) .
.
- 축구 선수 출신 기자가 말하는 스포츠계 폭력과 폐단

text:
i wanted my first post to come directly from my heart, thus i share with you the heart gallery. my platform for mrs. florida usa 2019 is to represent children and women who are victims of domestic violence. our strong survivors of the cruelty in this world. there is no one perhaps more vulnerable to this cruelty than children.
❤
a decade ago i stumbled upon the heart gallery which serves as an online platform to directly connect foster children with adoptive parents  in what they dream will be their forever home.
❤
this shook me to the core. i was in tears, in fact, i am never not in tears viewing these galleries. to me, it is an unimaginable quest to be a child on this earth and long for nothing more than parents to love and protect you. i wish i could be a mother to each and every one of these dear children. these amazing, incredible, survivors.
❤
my love for these child survivors catapulted me into my career as an attorney & child advocate. over this next year as mrs. florida usa i will represent these champions of hope and bring attention to their struggle with my voice. i hope that you will join me in my campaign to bring as much assistance and guidance to these amazing warriors as we can. to help prove to them that there are so many kind souls in this world that love and care for them. to assure them to hold on to their hope and follow their dreams! 
thank you for reading! ❤
very truly yours, 
krista lori thompson,  esq.
mrs. florida usa 2019 👸🏼🇺🇸 worldwide united

text:
harasment// продолжая тему предыдущих постов, хочется сказать, что в российском обществе практически не принято обращать внимание на приставания или домогательства на работе. чаще идет политика замалчивания, попытка убедить себя в том,что "ачотакова", "да это же просто флирт, а то будем, как в европах, зашугаем мужиков". почему-то никто не думает о чувствах того, кто подвергается таким домогательствам.

когда я не знала, как реагировать на "невинное" давай попьем вино у меня в номере, сказанное в 50-ый раз, то обратилась к друзьям мужского пола. кто-то посочувствовал, кто-то просто сказал "откажись, у нас не рабство", и только 1 человек сказал, что парням такие приставания ни о чем не говорят. они не могут девушку понять, в чем сложность, в чем дискомфорт. "ну откажись, ну не обращай внимание ". а потом через минуту:" ну вообще да, мужики же мстительные бывают ( как и женщины впрочем)". бинго!

и речь не о том, что надо соглашаться на какие-то предложения, а именно о последствиях. мало кто принимает отказ, начинаются придирки, приходится менять проект, отдел, а то и фирму.

я заметила, что в российских компаниях часто встречается незрелое hr, которое не реагирует на проблему. кто, что и кому говорит-не важно, только если ты не руководитель.
в зарубежных же много тренингов, как бороться, кому говорить и тд. хотя и это не 100% гарантия.

чтобы вы понимали, что проблема не надумана, в шапке профиля опубликовала ссылку на статью с историями про харасмент.
именно так называется сексуальное домогательство.

вы испытывали его когда-нибудь? или считаете, что это придумки эмансипированных женщин и слабых мужиков?

text:
هشتگ دو کاربرد مشخص و مهم دارد که حتی یکی از این دو کاربرد هم برای این‌که خود را به استفاده از آن عادت دهید کافی است
1- هشتگ پیش از هر چیز به بازدیدکننده فعلی عکس شما، توضیح می‌دهد که شما با چه انگیزه‌ای پست گذاشته‌اید و مطلب شما چه پیامی دارد
یک عکس مشخص با دو هشتگ مختلف می‌تواند دو پیام کاملاً متفاوت داشته باشد

2- کمک به اینستاگرام است تا محتوای پست شما را بهتر تشخیص دهد

هشتگ های پرکاربرد سال 2018
هشتگ metoo بیش از یک میلیون هفتصد هزار بار به اشتراک گذاشته شده که پرچم دار بزرگترین حماسه‌ی حمایت‌های هشتگی سالانه به شمار می‌رود‌. پس از آن، هشتگ timesup با 640000 بار استفاده و marchforourlives  با 568000 بار پست، در صدر قرار دارند

text:
⚜️о том, как хорошо терять друзей

ночные размышления💭решила записать📝
были времена,когда я коммуницировала достаточно активно и впускала в свою жизнь всех и каждого..не близко,конечно, но достаточно,чтобы считать таких людей своими «друзьями». и потом, когда эти «друзья» исчезали из моей жизни или исчезала я,мой пытливый ум никак не мог понять,почему так происходит,и где эта грань трансформации из приятеля в друга и наоборот? и почему такие «замечательные» личности вдруг начинают медленно «растворяться» из твоего поля зрения,словно крупицы сахара в чае?☕️
сейчас,благодаря работе над собой (и,наверное,отпечатку опыта и избирательности),я безумно радуюсь,что мне не нужно прилагать особых усилий, чтобы тот или иной индивидуум исчез из моей жизни,будто по волшебству,просто отсох и отвалился,как ненужный продукт жизнедеятельности.они это делают сами(низкий им поклон за это😌)
ведь такие люди не дают полноценно развиваться,тянут из тебя энергию,как паразиты 🦠 и,вообще,как пятое колесо телеге,т.е. ну никак🤭 с ними я-не я❗️.
ведь дружба и правильное окружение-это колоссальная работа над отношениями, чтобы они здорово функционировали. это подзарядка и простота, искренность, принятие тебя любого, лёгкость во всем😇
если человек меня не заряжает,и я не заряжаю его-это пустая трата времени и энергоресурсов.
пусть остаются те,кто достоин меня и кого достойна я.цените тех,кто рядом несмотря ни на что.это такая редкость в наши дни😌👍🏻.
.

сейчас,благодаря работе над собой (и,наверное,отпечатку опыта и избирательности),я безумно радуюсь,что мне не нужно прилагать особых усилий, чтобы тот или иной индивидуум исчез из моей жизни,будто по волшебству,просто отсох и отвалился,как ненужный продукт жизнедеятельности.они это делают сами(низкий им поклон за это😌)
ведь такие люди не дают полноценно развиваться,тянут из тебя энергию,как паразиты 🦠 и,вообще,как пятое колесо телеге,т.е. ну никак🤭 с ними я-не я❗️.
ведь дружба и правильное окружение-это колоссальная работа над отношениями, чтобы они здорово функционировали. это подзарядка и простота, искренность, принятие тебя любого, лёгкость во всем😇
если человек меня не заряжает,и я не заряжаю его-это пустая трата времени и энергоресурсов.
пусть остаются те,кто достоин меня и кого достойна я.цените тех,кто рядом несмотря ни на что.это такая редкость в наши дни😌👍🏻.
.

text:
** trigger alert** when i say you are worthy, don't settle for less, you are enough etc.... i'm not just throwing cute and fluffy words at you. i affirm your divinity because i know too well the dangers of a low self esteem. as a child i was sexually violated several times, i lost my mother at 9, bounced around from family to family and then from foster home to foster home. i was broken. i hated what i saw in the mirror and i went around searching for love and validation from all the wrong places. attracting relationships that mirrored the toxic beliefs that i had of myself. as a young adult i experienced domestic violence, cheated on and just accepted it as my reality. i gave birth to 4 children. i dpent 17 years with there father even though the relationship was falling apart. i stayed cause i knew if i left i would end up raising them on my on. i knew that i would end up being by myself because of fear that someone would do to them what was done to me. for years i went through life fearful and full of abandonment issues. somewhere along the way i started to heal. i walked away from people, situations and habit that wasn't serving me. i started to chose me....started to love me. it has been a long and at times a painful journey back to wholeness. but it's been worth it. i am worth it and so are you. in the spring i'll be 42, my oldest daughter will be 19, her sister 16 and i have 2 little boys. i thank god for grace. not only do i not look my age, i don't look like half the things i've been going through. that's why it's important for us to tell our testimony. because by god's grace most of us don't look like what we've been through.... grown through. 
romana

you’re at your emotional breaking point. maybe the worst has happened, or maybe it was just the “last straw”. the dbt distress tolerance skill you need is tipp. this skill is designed to bring you down from the metaphorical (hopefully not literal) ledge.

tipp stands for temperature, intense exercise, paced breathing, and paired muscle relaxation.

text:
have you tried unsuccessfully to heal your shame? discover how shame and control are intricately tied together; and that when you give up your attachment to control, you will find your shame disappearing.

many people on a healing path have found it extremely challenging to heal their shame. yet, when you understand the purpose of shame, you will be able to move beyond it.

shame is the feeling that there is something basically wrong with you. the feeling of guilt is about doing something wrong, whereas shame is about being wrong at the core. the feeling of shame comes from the belief that, “i am basically flawed, inadequate, wrong, bad, unimportant, undeserving or not good enough.” https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/01/28/why-we-feel-shame-and-how-to-conquer-it/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #trauma #therapydog #dissociativeidentitydisorder

text:
19/365
it’s taken me days to post this. @womensmarch is such an emotionally charged day for me. i feel all the feels. 2017: i was 9 months pregnant, marching in disbelief at the inauguration of dumb fuck in charge, with my two best girl friends and a sea of sisters. we marched because we literally didn’t know what else to do. we marched because we knew we had to do something. we marched before we knew the enormity and seriousness of what a trump presidency was really capable of. it was before #metoo and before #familiesbelongtogether and before #protectmueller. 2018: i marched with my baby earthside and my very best friend. we marched because we were mad. it was less organized, more angry. we marched and we couldn’t believe we still needed too. we were a year in and #metoo allegations abounded. we marched because we had to. 2019: this year i marched with my toddler and husband. we missed dearly our @morgantaylorbradley . this year we marched to remind ourselves and the world that we’re still here.  we may not know how to fix it, but we’re here and we care. we marched for babies separated from their mamas, which seems like so many catastrophes ago. we marched for dr blasey ford, because #webelievewomen. we marched for transgendered people in the military. we marched for homeless solutions. the issues confronting our world just keep compounding. and it feels more and more helpless. but i have to remember that there is light in the dark. we #tookbackthehouse and we have young, vibrant, diverse and female representation! we’ve got #speakerpelosi taking no prisoners and building no walls. we did that. 2020: i’m sure we’ll be marching again. hopefully with a roster of strong, progressive female voices running to replace this dumb fuck. whatever the cause or the campaign, we’ll be there for it.

text:
같이 만나고 #taranaburke의 #tedtalk와 같은 비디오를 보고 대화를 할 때 초점과 지원의 강력한 에너지입니다.

there’s a powerful energy and focus that supports us in our personal and collective endeavors when we watch & discuss videos like tarana burke’s tedtalk (founder of #metoo ). thanks for gathering us at the women of color content creators mashup, @byjessicanguyen of @projectvoicepod and @hausoftiffany of @spill_stories . ~
"the me too movement is a witch hunt." right? "me too is dismantling due process." or, "me too has created a gender war." the media has been consistent with headline after headline that frames this movement in ways that make it difficult to move our work forward, and right-wing pundits and other critics have these talking points that shift the focus away from survivors. so suddenly, a movement that was started to support all survivors of sexual violence is being talked about like it's a vindictive plot against men. 
but be clear: this is a movement about the one-in-four girls and the one-in-six boys who are sexually assaulted every year and carry those wounds into adulthood. it's about the 84 percent of trans women who will be sexually assaulted this year and the indigenous women who are three-and-a-half times more likely to be sexually assaulted than any other group. or people with disabilities, who are seven times more likely to be sexually abused. it's about the 60 percent of black girls like me who will be experiencing sexual violence before they turn 18, and the thousands and thousands of low-wage workers who are being sexually harassed right now on jobs that they can't afford to quit. 
this is a movement about the far-reaching power of empathy…trauma halts possibility. movement activates it.

so much of what we hear about the me too movement is about individual bad actors or depraved, isolated behavior, and it fails to recognize that anybody in a position of power comes with privilege, and it renders those without that power more vulnerable. we have to reeducate ourselves and our children to understand that power and privilege doesn't always have to destroy and take -- it can be used to serve and build.

text:
#bodydigging #golddigging #bodydigger (2 posts) #golddigger (218,088 posts) #doublestandards #metoo #feminism #hijab #mateselection #bodyobjectification #heterosexual #dating

why is it okay for a man to be a body digger, but it isn't okay for a woman to be a gold digger?

even though studies on mate selection, state that heterosexual men value women's bodies (their #beauty, #sexuality, and #fertility) most when selecting a mate -- they seem to have little self-awareness as to this fact. especially when the comparable practice for a woman value moat a man's resources and ability to protect, is severley put down.

it's unlikely that any one person's body or resources is going to satisfy everybody in the whole world. and it's likely that few people are going to like being valued for their body (women)  or resources (men) unless they are engaging in the exchange theory. people like sex workers, sugar daddies and sugar mamas, sugar babies and sugar boys are upfront about this exchange and i make no moral judgment. i think people should go after what they want. but what really irks me is the lack of understanding and awareness of men primarily valuing women's bodies and yet they denounce what women want.

oh yes, she should want him just for his body and maybe his personality. just never want him because he has wealth and status.

considering movies like the prince who pretends that he is a popper because he wants to make sure did the woman doesn't want him for his wealth and status. because who wants to be wanted for these superficial and shallow things? unless it is to benefit them.

and just like the movie shrek and the fat and ugly turning into a beautiful princess - people love the idea of being loved for the things that can't be seen too readily.

so unless you want to be fair about it, and you're okay with a woman taking advantage of your resources and your status - will you please take a moment to think about how your body digging affects women around the world?

text:
it’s time to change the narrative.  our children deserve better. this is not alright!!#timetoact #calltoaction

from ken austin of mercy house:

i am sure you have heard that another one of our young black males was shot and killed by a senseless act of violence while sleeping in his bed earlier this week. this is wrong on every level.  i can’t describe the pain and brokenness this family had to live through that night.  i held the mother’s and the 16 y/o twin sister’s hands while the officer gave them the official notification of death of their loved one.  no family in a civilized society should have to go through this ugliness.  we are burying our children too much, and these acts of violence are way too common among us. we will march together from common ground to the house that jaylan saunders lived in and was murdered in on the corner of hill street and dillard street. 
the enemies will come to know that we are fighters, and we are winners. #montgomery #gunviolence #marchforourlives #wokevote  #children #activist #blacklove #hbcu #hbculove #love #god #family #community #metoo #democrats #republicans #tuesdaymotivation #fathers #mothers #mymgm #riseup #eji #nationalurbanleague #myasu #troy #faulkner

text:
✨a l i g n m e n t✨ this came up on my tribe accountability call tonight and i had never really thought about it until one of us shared how she felt. at that time, i was like “🤔 that’s what was happening”. feeling misaligned for me equals questioning everything - even the things that are rock solid, feeling stressed about everything and a loss of control, and feeling like i can’t break out of the self doubt cycle. ⠀
.⠀
i think we’ve all been there but sometimes don’t quite realize what’s going on. that’s why it is so so so important to be really mindful of our thoughts, acknowledge what is fake (fear based) vs what is true (love) and what may be driving the feeling. it’s also important to give yourself compassion to feel through shitty emotions but reminding yourself that those things are impermanent and you will get through. ⠀
.⠀
wellness definitely started with nutrition for me but it is so much more. if you’re feeling something shitty, allow yourself to feel through it and i encourage you to share your feelings and be vulnerable. ⠀
.⠀
there are so many of us that can probably say “me too!!” to feeling a certain way at some point in our lives and can share what they did at that time to get through. you’re never alone.💛 ⠀
.⠀
feeling grateful for a few things: this sunny mid 60s weather, having a fiancé to support me when i’m feeling wedding budget stress (thanks babe😘), a health food grocery store only a mile from our house, and being a part of a tribe of inspiring women that make me feel a little less crazy and fully, without judgement, support me in becoming my best self. seriously words do not express how grateful i am for your souls.💜👯‍♀️⠀
.⠀
.⠀

text:
this is the face of ptsd. unedited, unfiltered, unable to be apologetic even if it wanted to. 
it has been a long time since something has triggered my negative thought patterns associated with ptsd, but tonight it hit me hard. the kicker is that it was a simple, every day conversation that set me off. i've been speaking of ptsd in the past tense for years and tonight made me realize it can never be past tense, it is and will always be the harbinger of fear at the back of my mind. 
i am a strong, independent, hard-working woman and because of this it is often assumed that i'm not susceptible to the same emotions other women feel. the reality is that i have been so scarred by my past that i've built a wall inside myself to hold all of these emotions at bay, and on the outside i am composed and logical. when the ptsd is triggered and the negative thought patterns take hold - i freeze. just like i did that day so many years ago. the thoughts revolve in a never ending cycle of bad to worse and i shut down. until i finally register: this is a symptom of my ptsd and i am creating these scenarios because of my fear of being hurt again. "i must not fear. fear is the mind killer. fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration. i will face my fear. i will permit it to pass over me and through me and when it has gone past, i will turn the inner eye to see it's path. where the fear has gone there will be nothing. only i will remain." dune, frank herbert. 
#ptsd #fear #dune #frankherbert #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #thisiswhatptsdlookslike #negativethoughts #cbt #stopthepattern #mantra #iamstronger #metoo

text:
the newest edition of my novel ‘sketches from the heart of a texas artist: the love necklace edition,’ is a true testament to the purpose behind the @love_necklace_campaign
we all travel through darkness at some point or another and it looks different to everyone.  you cannot judge another’s journey, but you can offer love, and kindness, and compassion.
🌴
this story is about a woman who is battling with her own anxieties and is being chased by a dark shadow.  this is her adventure as she embarks upon a journey back into the light. 🌴
does she accept her vulnerability? yes.  is it a terrifying journey? yes.  does she make mistakes? yes.  is it all worth it?  you’ll have to read to find out, but i will tell you that any journey back into the light, in the wake of trauma, is never going to be easy... it is going to be filled with villains and threshold guardians and shape shifters, and jokers, and you may lose yourself several times along the way...
🌴
... but i think that, in the end, we'd all agree that the adventure was worth it. #love #storytelling #faith #trust .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
我們人生當中有一個影響圈和關注圈，影響圈就是你做的是力所能及可以改變的東西。關注圈是你只能評論只能發表意見只能生悶氣，但是沒用的改變不了東西。
所以一個積極的人應該把精力放在哪個圈子，這是我認爲古往今來所有的成功人士唯一的共同之處。就是把精力放在影響圈當中做事，如果你天天焦慮，痛苦，罵別人，指責，找借口。哪你的影響圈的社會會變得越來越小。這就是孔子講的君子求諸己小人求諸人
專注力一定要放在影響圈當中，這才是最重要的。
先放大石頭還是先放小石頭？我們生活中有特別多的人就是被大量的小事而佔據我們每天耗費了很多的時間。－－－－－樊登讀書會

text:
mujer :
*libérate de todo lo malo
*sé como tú quieras, si quieres ponerte un vestido , hazlo con la seguridad de que te sientes cómoda y hermosa , ya que lo haces por ti no por los demás *si quieres usar tacones, que suenen firmes tus pasos, para demostrar que tienes seguridad en tu vida.
*si quieres usar los labios pintados , hazlo!!! porque créeme , te ves preciosa porque a ti te gusta *si quieres bailar descalzos , hazlo!! ya que de cualquier manera puedes liberar la felicidad que provoca  en ti...
* *si quieres ser tu , hazlo! nada ni nadie puede prohibirte ser como eres , cómo quieres , cómo tú esencia lo dicte !!! nadie es dueño de tu vida más a tu misma ,
no dejes que nadie opaque esa hermosa sonrisa, porque créeme , mereces ser feliz ❤️ tarde o temprano llegará a tu vida quien ame cada parte de ti , cada defecto, cada virtud !!! y será en ese momento cuando digas que todo lo que dejaste atrás, será una enseñanza en la vida para que seas más fuerte y feliz en un futuro
#niunamenos #metoo #yositecreo

text:
fire 
as a little girl i dared to dream,
of growing up and living in a world not my own.
i was told as a young girl that a woman is equal to a man! 
i went out into the world and left my home.
i left my father behind with the most ignorant beliefs. 
he would say “ i trust you sweetheart, it’s other people i don’t trust”.
but i would roll my eyes, scoff and reply
“dad, you can trust me to know other people and who i can and cannot trust”.
i walked towards my future carrying this reality on my shoulders,
the world i was told to grow into. 
i was alone, not in a city i called home. 
i was too friendly, 
and when they got too close that they touched.
i got burned. 
fire

i have scares on my soul, rage seared into righteous flesh. 
virgin skin now stained with charred memories branded into nightmares. 
fire wanting to vomit its way out of my body in fury. 
it’s too much at once to stop. 
hold me. don’t touch me. 
get your hands off me. 
this is my body. 
i own me. 
you don’t know me. 
no.
you can’t have me. 
no. 
you can’t touch me. 
no. 
i don’t need to explain myself. 
fire 
so don’t you dare tell me to calm down or to cool my fire.
don’t act like i’m to explosive.
who do you think you are? 
if you don’t like it, that’s a fucking you problem.
with reckoning tears spilling from my eyes
i will spit hot hell fire from my lips when someone tries to slip 
their fingers up my skirt when i walk by them at the club. 
i will no longer hold my tongue back from the lashes it gives the men who throw beer on me and 2 am on a cold winter night. 
i will not allow my words to turn to smoke when i’ve been hit across the face and i will not cool my fire when i have been wronged. 
i will not cease to burn too hot to touch when you try to touch that which is not your to touch! 
my body 
not to be taken as an object,

text:
via @foxnashville: 
a survey by the violence policy venter says tennessee is 4th in the nation for men killing women in domestic-related homicides.

on saturday, one survivor walked through the streets with bruises all over her face to bring attention to the problem.

it's 2 p.m. in the gulch.

sparkle johnson and her kids are sitting on the bench, wondering if anybody will ask her if she's okay.
her face is covered in bruises after her husband's last attack. “the cut of the scissors or from the dvd that he was slicing at me,” she said.

she then gets up to cross the street, and – finally – a man comes up to her. “everything okay? you sure? what's up? what's your name, darling?” he asks.

he asks her how he can help. “make sure you get the cops involved first,” he says, “because that's going to be the first place that's going to put him behind bars.
she tells him the bruises are fake, but the story is real – a direct reenactment of how she looked after her last attack. “anything that could be done, was done, except for taking my life. i wasn't shot, but i was shot at. he forced me to play russian roulette and put the gun in my mouth. he beat me, he raped me, cut me,” johnson said.  she then walked through the crowd of people taking pictures with the famous wings; hundreds of people, and not a single question. “they pointed, they whispered, but nobody offered to help me. even one lady, she stopped to let my son pet her dog but she didn't even acknowledge what was happening.”
.
.
.

text:
getting treated poorly doesn’t mean you are required to take the punches.
.
if you have a quiet demeanour, or if there’s something about you that others find threatening to their own self-worth, you will find your limits being tested. not because there’s anything wrong with you, but because you stand out.
.
some people will push and push to see how far you can go before you finally decide to stand your ground. that’s how bullies operate. they see something in you that they lack in themselves. it terrifies them. they probe your weaknesses—and once they see an opening, they go in for the kill like a predator.
.
when your rights are being challenged, it’s okay to speak up and let your voice be heard. but it’s equally important to do it in a way that is non-destructive while still allowing you to preserve your respect, dignity, and class. no one is ever worth tarnishing your own character over.
.
when you’re honest in your approach and stay calm, cool, and collected, you will be amazed at the amount of respect you earn—especially from those who initially made you feel inferior. your actions end up speaking volumes about the kind of person you are and it makes others question the way they conduct themselves. and a tone that was once higher than yours loses its power.
.
who they are should never stop you from smiling. they should never stop you from being your best self. they should never stop you from treating other people right.
.
it’s crucial to understand that how people choose to behave is a direct reflection of their own character, their own projections, their own insecurities. what they do or say has absolutely nothing to do with you and everything to do with them.
.
don’t feel bad when someone treats you a certain way. don’t carry blame inside of you. don’t allow the pain they haven’t confronted to become yours. leave that burden with its rightful owner. any form of abuse is not to be tolerated. if they attempt to disrupt your peace, you say what you need to say and walk away with your head held high. and if you need support, seek it.
.
when you own a situation and choose not to surrender to defeat, the control they might’ve thought they had is over.

text:
at least once a day i hear someone in my life use the phrase “i feel out of control” or “i avoided ____ because i feared being out of control”. .
here’s is a little, well-known, secret though. our sense of control is never built in the big things. it is always built in the small things. .
take a moment today and narrate what your doing by adding in where you have control. .
in this moment, as i drive to work/school, i have control of what i listen to, how loud i play it, if i skip or not. i am in control of which direction i take, how quickly i drive, if i use my turn signals, or honk at another driver. .
it’s amazing how something so mundane and at times thoughtless activity is a foundation to recognize our control, our power, in our lives.
.
.
.
. . .

text:
sexual response stage 4: resolution 😌
.
according to the center for healthy sex, the body slowly returns to its normal level of functioning during resolution. swollen and erect body parts return to their previous size and color. this phase is marked by a general sense of well-being, enhanced intimacy and, often, fatigue. 😊💕😴
.
cue the cuddle chemicals! #oxytocin #4life 💖💓💗
.
for those of us with female organs, we have no refractory period. this makes multiple orgasms possible, as opposed to those with male organs. #winning
.
it's important to note that not all sexual experiences lead to orgasm, and this shouldn't be the goal in mind when exploring sex and sexuality. ✔
.
more on that later! for now, we rest. it's sunday, after all 😉 #dayofrest
.
